commit a649e476effe05e3bc42fe87dec4a4cf28f1adea
Author: claude (dev65 78b46e5b-02ea-4aa0-8b4a-115f1bffb8d1) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 9 10:55:46 2026 -0400

    ci: fix 4 mock-API tests that asserted the un-sanitized '->' arrow

    github-org-fork / dm-github-* route every plan message through log(), which pipes
    it through sanitize-string (helper-scripts). sanitize-string maps '>' to '_' as
    display-injection hardening, so a plan line's '->' arrow reaches the output as
    '-_'. These four tests grep for the raw '->' fragment and so fail ('missing
    expected fragment'), while all the other tests in the suite already assert
    sanitizer-safe content.

    Sanitize each expected fragment the same way (pipe through sanitize-string) before
    matching, so the assertion pins the tool's intended message rather than
    sanitize-string's glyph mapping (which helper-scripts owns and tests). Needles stay
    readable with '->'. sanitize-string is a no-op on the non-arrow fragments, so only
    the arrow lines change behaviour.

    Full ci/tests suite: 30 passed, 0 failed (was 26 passed, 4 failed). Not related to
    the R-074 work merged in #139; these were pre-existing failures.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

