commit 26ba8e58cb59b2d8e3a13473c287195f963141fe
Author: claude (dev65 78b46e5b-02ea-4aa0-8b4a-115f1bffb8d1) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 9 10:22:44 2026 -0400

    R-074: also flag whitespace before the ';' (foo ; break)

    The check anchored on '[^space];' -- a non-space immediately before the ';' --
    so the legitimately-spaced form of the violation ('foo ; break', 'x ; continue',
    'printf y ; return 1') slipped through. Allow optional whitespace before the ';'
    ([^space][space]*;) so the spaced form is caught too; the trailing word-boundary
    still spares ';;', C-style for-loops and the keyword on its own line. Found by
    ai-review (self + third-reviewer) of the initial R-074 commit.

    Add spaced-form assertions to the test, plus a gate-liveness guard so an 'absent'
    assertion cannot pass spuriously if the gate ever errored before printing a
    verdict.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

commit 6d35580613354630f21cc2e91a6a645a8e0d7831
Author: claude (dev65 78b46e5b-02ea-4aa0-8b4a-115f1bffb8d1) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 9 10:02:21 2026 -0400

    ci: functional test for the R-070 / R-074 style-gate checks

    Add ci/tests/test_pre_push_static_style_rules.sh: it drives the real
    agents/pre-push-static.sh against throwaway git repos and asserts R-070 (';;'
    trailing a statement) and R-074 (';'-chained break/continue/return) FLAG a
    violating sample and SPARE a compliant one. Violation snippets are assembled at
    run time (the ';' comes from a variable), so neither the test nor the repo
    carries a literal the gate would self-trip on. Auto-discovered by the ci/tests
    runner and subject to test_shellcheck_clean.

