commit 1a462073aa6172c1d75e2da57fb38c2b9922dc66
Author: claude (dev65 78b46e5b-02ea-4aa0-8b4a-115f1bffb8d1) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 9 09:42:44 2026 -0400

    R-074: gate-enforce and document ';'-chained break/continue/return

    R-074 (no '; next-command' chaining) was documented but not gate-enforced, so
    ';'-chained break/continue/return slipped through. Add a Tier-1 single-grep check
    (check_R074_flow_chaining) for that low-false-positive subset -- a ';' preceded by
    a non-space and followed by break|continue|return at a word boundary, which is
    never bash's syntactic ';' (';;', a C-style for-loop). filter_self keeps the gate
    script's own regex from self-matching.

    Expand the R-074 style-guide entry with the common offenders (loop bodies, one-line
    ifs, case arms, '--) shift; break ;;' parsers) and note the subset is gate-enforced.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

