commit a8b364569182ffb07c4a7438214aacb24fdf2a78
Author: claude (dev66 8bd92be9-9ef9-445b-84c0-4c454d528432) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 8 18:39:22 2026 -0400

    docs: dm-consumer.yml is a shared overlay - merge, never overwrite

    Add explicit editing guidance to the consumer-templates spec:
    dm-consumer.yml accumulates one independent top-level key per opted-in
    template (coverity:, dist-ai-tests:, ...), so a key change must MERGE
    into the existing file, never rewrite it from a single template's
    fragment.

    Documents a real regression: a commit adding dist-ai-tests: overwrote
    helper-scripts' dm-consumer.yml and dropped the pre-existing coverity:
    block, leaving the Coverity workflow running with no project-name /
    canonical-repos. CI stayed green; the scan just went nowhere - the
    easy-to-miss failure mode this note warns against.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

