commit 79616bb1c13769746cae72b178e3e1d124093e4e
Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) (Machine Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 7 07:48:58 2026 -0400

    reusable-dist-ai-tests: sibling checkout layout to fix pytest collection

    The caller repo was checked out at the workspace root with dist-ai
    nested at .dist-ai inside it. A suite that runs pytest (privleap-tests)
    derives the test module name from the path relative to rootdir; the
    leading-dot .dist-ai component yielded a leading-dot module name and
    pytest failed collection with "the 'package' argument is required to
    perform a relative import". Check the component, dist-ai, and
    developer-meta-files out as sibling subdirs (component/, dist-ai/, dmf/)
    instead, and point --component-root at component/. Keeps the suite path
    out of the caller tree and free of dot components.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

commit 811031b56291103df8e4fa63646401196e6bb9e7
Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) (Machine Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Tue Jul 7 07:35:10 2026 -0400

    CI: add reusable-dist-ai-tests.yml + consumer template

    Reusable workflow that runs a package's comprehensive dist-ai regression
    suites (which live in org-ai-assisted/dist-ai, not in-tree) against the
    package's own PRs and master pushes, via
    dist-ai-tests-all --component/--component-root. The component is derived
    from the caller repo name, so the consumer wrapper is universal
    (byte-identical, no .github/dm-consumer.yml). Ships the byte-identical
    consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-dist-ai-tests.yml for
    propagation by pkg_update_consumer_workflows.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

