    Fresh-context reviewer (real): the submodule inner 'git diff' (and the main
    --stat) were written to the terminal WITHOUT stcat -- a terminal-escape
    injection vector for the textual reviewer, unlike every other untrusted line
    here. Pipe both through stcat (pipefail keeps a git failure loud). Also gate the
    GIT_REVIEW_UNICODE_NONFATAL deferral in git_review_finish on
    git_review_display_terminal_safe, so a GUI viewer now fails closed IMMEDIATELY on
    a fatal blob (matching the comments) rather than deferring.

    Codex (real): with mergetool.review-meld trustExitCode=false, git ignored the
    wrapper's fail-closed refuse-exit and fell back to a "was the merge successful?"
    prompt where a careless "y" resolves an unreviewed binary/undecodable conflict.
    Fix: git-review-mergetool now determines resolution ITSELF (did $MERGED change?),
    so both mergetool entries use trustExitCode=true -- honoring the refuse-exit AND
    correctly handling meld's unreliable exit code (0 on close-without-save).

    Codex (rejected, again): "restore the relative-libexec fallback" -- the bare
    absolute source path is the deliberate package convention.

    Verified installed: git-meld-tests 0 hidden-change failures; difftool/mergetool
    13/13; new guards for submodule-escape neutralization and mergetool
    saved-vs-unsaved authoritative exit.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

