commit f8e6bd2e22797c1e11382f1adb9a05cda4a6bee6
Author: claude (dist-encrypted 32346333-8fef-4cd4-8c75-bad674a69df0) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Jul 3 12:45:41 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: R-103 flags only command-position exec, not 'docker exec'

    R-103 (no process-replacement 'exec') matched any '<space>exec<space>' token, so
    it false-flagged 'exec' used as a SUBCOMMAND ARGUMENT -- 'docker exec',
    'kubectl exec', 'nsenter ... exec' -- which is not bash process replacement at
    all. The only escape was a per-script allow-exec waiver, i.e. suppressing a real
    rule to dodge a false positive.

    Match only COMMAND-POSITION exec instead: at line start, or right after a command
    separator (; & | && || ( ) { }) or a control keyword (then/do/else/in). A bareword
    before 'exec' (a command name) no longer matches. fd-redirection exec stays exempt
    via the trailing class; the allow-exec waiver stays for genuine process-handoff
    surfaces.

    Net effect vs the old regex: drops the docker/kubectl/nsenter false positives AND
    newly catches a real case the old pattern missed -- subshell '(exec cmd)'.
    Verified against a fixture of positive (line-start / post-separator / post-keyword
    / subshell) and negative (docker/kubectl/sudo exec, fd-redirect, comment,
    substring) cases.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_011nGFGA6Qhi8prJkLrp1EDw

