commit 80c5ff2939aae75b32fce98291961e88facf4db3
Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 09:14:12 2026 -0400

    git-meld: surface mode/symlink/gitlink-spoof/Trojan-Unicode; pre-flight for skipped files

    Harden the diff driver against review evasion (a diff tool must never render a
    real change as empty/misleading output). Driven by adversarial + fuzz tests
    (dist-ai): the old driver hid mode-only changes, symlink swaps, Trojan-Source
    Unicode, and files git skips; all now surfaced.

    Driver path:
    - MODE CHANGE banner when old/new mode differ (e.g. a data file made +x) --
      a content diff alone never shows this.
    - SYMLINK: print old->new link target (meld would show it as innocuous text)
      and stop, instead of handing a link to meld as a file.
    - Decide the submodule branch by MODE (160000), NOT by blob content: a regular
      file whose content merely reads 'Subproject commit <hex>' is a spoof to route
      a real file change through the (meld-less) submodule path -- now warned and
      treated as a regular file. Real gitlinks use 'git -C' (not 'cd') + a repo
      check, so an odd/symlinked submodule path cannot redirect us.
    - Trojan-Source scan: warn on bidirectional/invisible/control Unicode in the
      new blob before opening meld.
    - Argument-mode sanity warning.

    Re-dispatch ('git meld') path:
    - Pre-flight 'git diff --no-ext-diff --stat --summary --find-renames' overview,
      the only way to surface files git never hands to the driver (marked
      binary/-diff/diff= by .gitattributes, auto-binary via a NUL byte, LFS). Warn
      loudly when .gitattributes itself changes.

    Verified: adversarial suite 0 hidden (was 4), fuzzer 0 hidden over 150 iters
    (was 3); no regression on the submodule suite; shellcheck + gate clean.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
