commit 188f4b847d331a726de8065730620dabe3aa7fed
Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 08:20:26 2026 -0400

    git-meld: fix submodule diff (--no-ext-diff placement); never hide a change; export counter

    Three git-meld fixes:

    - SECURITY / hidden-change: the submodule inner diffs were wrapped in
      '|| true', so any failure was swallowed and the reviewer saw EMPTY
      output -- a real (possibly malicious) submodule pointer change rendered
      as "no change". A review/diff tool must never do that. Now the gitlink
      transition 'Submodule <path>: <old> -> <new>' is always printed first,
      and a diff failure fails LOUD (error to stderr + exit 1) instead of
      being hidden. Verified with an adversarial sandbox test (unfetched
      old/new/both commits): 0 hidden-change cases, vs all hidden before.

    - '--no-ext-diff' was in the wrong position: 'git --no-ext-diff diff' is
      rejected ("unknown option: --no-ext-diff") because it is a 'git diff'
      option, not a top-level git option. So the submodule diffs ALWAYS
      failed -- the feature never worked, and '|| true' masked that too.
      Moved it after 'diff' ('git diff --no-ext-diff ...') in both branches.

    - export git_external_level so the recursion-depth guard actually works:
      it was never exported, so a re-invoked driver reset the count to 1 and
      the '>= 3' guard could never fire. Kept the START/END level markers.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01FhPYFwuCtfJn3tJJHstoXg

commit 05ea8d09f97b306df59d5b26cef18f89cb9ae1f7
Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 08:14:31 2026 -0400

    dm-virtualbox...wiki-links: don't abort on a missing link; real multi-URL warning

    Two correctness fixes from an AI-review pass:

    - errexit-abort: replace_wiki_string was called as a bare command in
      main(). It returns non-zero when the current URL is absent from the
      page (nothing to replace), which under 'set -o errexit' aborted the
      ENTIRE run -- skipping the remaining links, the second wiki, and the
      local download.txt / SHA256SUMS writes. Guard each call in an 'if',
      warn-and-continue, and only mark the page dirty on a successful
      replace.

    - dead multi-URL warning: extract_url overwrote its result each
      iteration and emitted a single line, so callers' '[ ${#result[@]} !=
      1 ]' ambiguity check could never fire and a page with several matches
      silently took the last. extract_url now emits every match, one per
      line; callers distinguish 0 (no URL) / 1 (ok) / many (ambiguous) and
      read result[0] nounset-safely.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01FhPYFwuCtfJn3tJJHstoXg

commit d1df81cebc15bd647d5d56cc9dd15769fedf669b
Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 07:57:10 2026 -0400

    dm-virtualbox...wiki-links: write wiki tmpfile with 'overwrite', not 'append-once'

    'append-once <file> <content>' on the fresh empty mktemp used to stage
    the wiki page prepends a newline: append_shared reads the empty file,
    sees it does not end in "\n", "fixes" that by setting contents to "\n",
    then appends -- leaving a blank line at the top. This happened in both
    replace_wiki_string and save_cached_page_to_wiki, so leading blank lines
    accumulated on the uploaded wiki page (one per changed link + one on
    save). Tested: 3 replaces + save produced 4 leading blank lines.

    'overwrite' is the correct tool -- it truncates and writes the content
    verbatim (with a single trailing newline), skipping the empty-file
    newline fixup, so the page starts at its first real line. Tested: same
    flow now yields 0 leading blank lines, content intact. Dropped the now-
    unused 'append-once' dependency check.

    Pre-existing since the file was first added (7932da50), not introduced
    by the recent both-wikis / has-die changes.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
