commit 480d473e7d34a1a4f36f5b3f53329ba7a926ea74
Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 06:06:37 2026 -0400

    bash-style-guide R-103: prefer the plain command over the rc= dance

    The R-103 "Good" example showed a capture-and-exit pattern

        rc=0
        cmd ... || rc=$?
        exit "${rc}"

    for the last-line handoff that replaces `exec cmd`. That is
    unnecessary ceremony there: a script's exit status is its last
    command's exit status, so a plain call forwards the code already,
    and under 'set -o errexit' a failure exits with the child's status
    while any 'trap ... EXIT' cleanup still runs (what exec skips).

    Make the plain call the primary "Good" form, and keep the explicit
    '|| rc=$?' capture only for its real use: running inline cleanup on
    every exit path and still returning the child's original code (there
    the '|| rc=$?' is load-bearing -- it disarms errexit so teardown
    runs). The R-103 static check only forbids 'exec <command>'; it does
    not require the dance, so the plain call already passes.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01FhPYFwuCtfJn3tJJHstoXg

