commit 6233ad270dfb26349d04f42f69cb1613dd2de2b4
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 19:18:21 2026 -0400

    dm-prepare-release: pass export-chroot vars via --preserve-env, not an env-file

    virtualbox_export serialized the build variables to a 'chroot-env-export-vbox-vm'
    file ('{ ...; declare -p; } > file') that the chroot export script sourced --
    runtime-generated code. Instead export the allowlisted variables plus the
    export-specific presentation strings (producturl, vendor, ...) and let the
    existing '--preserve-env' on the cowbuilder call carry them into the chroot;
    drop the env-file argument. Pairs with the derivative-maker change to the
    chroot scripts. Verified end to end (kicksecure-cli/virtualbox dry-run: export
    runs with no env file, OVA produced, exit 0).

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

