commit 58032a8c59cb5feddc6cb0da3a80500ee9abfe43
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 18:39:32 2026 -0400

    dm-check-unicode: simplify helper-scripts path + git-symlink enumeration

    Two readability cleanups, no behavior change (dm-check-unicode still exits 0
    clean, whonix-workstation symlink still handled):

    - Drop the superfluous 'helper_scripts_dir' alias: it was just
      "HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH or its in-tree default" under another name. Default
      HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH itself and export it, so run-via-helper-scripts inherits
      this same tree instead of re-deriving its own.

    - Replace the 'while ... done < <(git ls-files ... | awk ...)' process
      substitution with a captured variable iterated via a here-string. Capturing
      first lets errexit catch a git failure (the process substitution masked it);
      the tab split + a '${meta%% *}' parameter expansion read the mode, dropping
      the awk 'split()' entirely; and with no subshell around the loop the
      associative array is populated in the current shell.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

