commit 1d8958737d389aff16d7f5f0cc72a65f29f0e1ed
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 16:06:16 2026 -0400

    git-meld --no-ext-diff; dm-check-unicode/dm-prepare-release env + rename cleanup

    - git-meld: pass --no-ext-diff to the inner 'git diff' calls. git propagates
      the top-level '-c diff.external=git-meld' to nested git via
      GIT_CONFIG_PARAMETERS, so without it the submodule/blob diffs re-enter this
      driver (popping meld per file / hitting the recursion guard) instead of
      printing the normal textual diff.
    - dm-prepare-release: the chroot env file passed to the export chroot script is
      now framed as serialized data (declare -x restored via 'source'), without a
      '#!/bin/bash' shebang -- it was never executed as a script. Add a
      'style-ok: no-has' waiver for the pre-existing 'command -v' dependency probes.
    - dm-check-unicode: follow the helper-scripts-run -> run-via-helper-scripts
      rename (var, path, comments).

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

commit b31e7c914afe02ef54e42d59354a7426e95030e0
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 15:26:13 2026 -0400

    git-meld: add git external diff driver

    A dual-mode git diff driver moved in from a local ~/bin script and brought up
    to the bash style guide:
    - opens 'meld' for regular files;
    - for a submodule gitlink change, cd's into the submodule and prints its own
      'git diff' between the old and new commits (instead of the opaque
      "Subproject commit <hex>" blob);
    - invoked without GIT_DIFF_PATH_TOTAL (i.e. as 'git meld ...' via a delegating
      alias) it re-execs 'git diff' with itself wired in as diff.external, using a
      self-referential path so it works in-tree and installed.

    Robustness: a one-argument guard for git's unmerged-path callback (avoids a
    nounset abort during conflict review), hex-only submodule-commit extraction
    (tolerates the '-dirty' suffix), and a recursion-depth guard.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

commit 0e3010844aa22e2d9f452aa4cbe6f95acccb85eb
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 13:37:45 2026 -0400

    dm-prepare-release: export VirtualBox OVA inside the cowbuilder chroot

    The VirtualBox VM is created and registered inside the amd64 cowbuilder
    chroot (see derivative-maker build-steps.d/*_create-vbox-vm), and
    VirtualBox is no longer installed on the build host. So factor the
    VBoxManage-using portion of virtualbox_export out of the host: it now
    serializes the build environment and dispatches to a chroot script
    (help-steps/pbuilder-chroot-script-export-vbox-vm in derivative-maker)
    via cowbuilder --execute. The .ova is written to the bind-mounted
    binary_image_ova_file so it lands on the host; signing and upload stay on
    the host where the operator credentials already are.

    Also drop the Whonix-External / Whonix-Internal libvirt network XML files
    from the multi-VM release archive and its test -f checks: those files were
    removed from the libvirt-dist package, so they are no longer generated.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

commit b6b5e5cd0ff3361fa0d31e26a8cc3e7186740376
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 30 06:35:07 2026 -0400

    dm-check-unicode: handle git symlinks independent of core.symlinks

    With core.symlinks=false a git-tracked symlink (mode 120000) is checked
    out as a regular text file whose content is the link target. The old code
    found symlinks via 'find -type l' (which misses those), so it never
    verified them against the whitelist, and the missing-newline check then
    false-flagged them. One path (qubes/qubes-template-whonix/whonix-workstation)
    was special-cased by shelling out to a bare 'stcat', which is not on PATH
    in the dry-run CI container -- so the 1200 caller misreported the
    resulting "command not found" as "Unicode found!".

    Enumerate symlinks from git metadata instead:
    - git ls-files --recurse-submodules --stage, filtered to mode 120000,
      gives every tracked symlink regardless of core.symlinks (and across
      submodules).
    - read_link_target() reads the target via readlink for a real symlink, or
      via the security-hardened helper-scripts 'stcat' for the regular-file
      materialization, run through the new 'helper-scripts-run' wrapper (which
      sets HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH + PYTHONPATH) so it resolves during the build
      bootstrap, before helper-scripts is installed, without losing stcat's
      hardening. Requires the helper-scripts helper-scripts-run change.
    - find_symlinks() verifies the git symlink set (plus any stray filesystem
      symlinks) against the whitelist; it prunes only real '.git' directories
      ('-path "*/.git" -prune'), no longer over-excluding '.github/' etc.
    - The missing-newline check skips git-tracked symlinks generically,
      replacing the single hardcoded special-case.

    Verified: with core.symlinks=false, dm-check-unicode passes on a clean
    tree (exit 0), reads whonix-workstation via the in-tree stcat, and no
    longer flags it.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

