Author: claude (derivative-maker b0dfc869-1cb7-42f6-8aa8-8ad1eafa0b81) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jul 2 03:45:34 2026 -0400

    dm-virtualbox-update-local-and-wiki-links: update both wikis

    The VirtualBox host software installation template is mirrored on both
    the Kicksecure and Whonix wikis with an identical page title; only the
    domain differs. The script only updated www.kicksecure.com and carried a
    dead '## TODO / ## XXX: hardcoded' commented-out mw-edit for
    www.whonix.org.

    Iterate the full fetch/compare/save cycle over a wiki_url_list holding
    both domains instead of bolting on a second hardcoded mw-edit. Each wiki
    is tracked independently: its current page content is fetched and
    compared per wiki (the wiki_cache key already includes WIKI_URL), so a
    wiki that is already current is left untouched. Renamed
    kicksecure_wiki_vbox_page to wiki_vbox_page since it is no longer
    Kicksecure-specific, and dropped the dead whonix comment.

