        Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

    commit 6b97215782d090661e7126cca3aee9911edf901f
    Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Date:   Tue Jun 30 06:35:07 2026 -0400

        dm-check-unicode: handle git symlinks independent of core.symlinks

        With core.symlinks=false a git-tracked symlink (mode 120000) is checked
        out as a regular text file whose content is the link target. The old code
        found symlinks via 'find -type l' (which misses those), so it never
        verified them against the whitelist, and the missing-newline check then
        false-flagged them. One path (qubes/qubes-template-whonix/whonix-workstation)
        was special-cased by shelling out to a bare 'stcat', which is not on PATH
        in the dry-run CI container -- so the 1200 caller misreported the
        resulting "command not found" as "Unicode found!".

        Enumerate symlinks from git metadata instead:
        - git ls-files --recurse-submodules --stage, filtered to mode 120000,
          gives every tracked symlink regardless of core.symlinks (and across
          submodules).
        - read_link_target() reads the target via readlink for a real symlink, or
          via the security-hardened helper-scripts 'stcat' for the regular-file
          materialization, run through the new 'helper-scripts-run' wrapper (which
          sets HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH + PYTHONPATH) so it resolves during the build
          bootstrap, before helper-scripts is installed, without losing stcat's
          hardening. Requires the helper-scripts helper-scripts-run change.
        - find_symlinks() verifies the git symlink set (plus any stray filesystem
          symlinks) against the whitelist; it prunes only real '.git' directories
          ('-path "*/.git" -prune'), no longer over-excluding '.github/' etc.
        - The missing-newline check skips git-tracked symlinks generically,
          replacing the single hardcoded special-case.

        Verified: with core.symlinks=false, dm-check-unicode passes on a clean
        tree (exit 0), reads whonix-workstation via the in-tree stcat, and no
        longer flags it.

        Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
        Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

commit f65f74667459a5677393ff8a5678ca663ae0486f
Author: claude (dev29 1b766332-1023-4a87-adbd-b17a64476bbf) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 15:21:12 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: add R-034 (no echo) + R-103 (no process-replacement exec)

    Two more Tier-1 gate rules, with the established script-wide waiver shape:

    - R-034: 'echo' used as a command (use printf, per R-030). echo is not
      portable -- -n/-e and backslash handling differ across shells, and data
      with a leading '-' or a '\' silently changes the output. Waiver:
      ## style-ok: allow-echo.
    - R-103: process-replacement 'exec <command>' (run it as a child and forward
      the exit code, so the wrapper stays in the ps tree and its cleanup runs).
      fd-redirection exec ('exec 9>lock', 'exec {fd}>&-', 'exec >log') is NOT
      process replacement and is exempt. Waiver: ## style-ok: allow-exec.

    Both checks are per-script (waiver-aware), exclude comments, and are
    filter_self'd (their needle/tag text appears in this script). Documents
    R-034/R-103 in bash-style-guide.md.

    Drive-by: the header-comment additions pushed 'shopt -s shift_verbose' to
    line 101, just past R-010's head-100 window (the gate then flagged its own
    5/6 block); trimmed the additions so the strict block stays within 100.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01BBdc6EqGiW8uGCQsvkn8LD

commit 840cb6090312ca4dbd2a80adc181027406896516
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 12:05:11 2026 -0400

    dm-packaging-helper-script: unify upstream remote mapping (review)

    CodeRabbit (PR #125) flagged that pkg_git_diff_and_merge_branch_upstream
    derived the upstream remote as 'github-<project>', but the pull path maps
    'derivative-maker' to 'github-kicksecure' (there is no
    'github-derivative-maker' remote) -- so the merge path silently no-op'd for
    the derivative-maker project.

    Extract the mapping into a single pkg_git_upstream_remote() helper and reuse
    it from the merge wrapper, the trusted-upstream dispatch match, and the pull
    function, so the three cannot diverge.

