commit b733f5ed496944342a1bf430e7ef30eff5a86851
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 11:44:32 2026 -0400

    dm-packaging-helper-script: fix upstream pull/merge git plumbing

    Three fixes in the upstream-sync helpers:

    - pkg_git_branch_pull_upstream_master: 'origin_name_list' was declared local
      but never populated, so the pull loop iterated an empty array and pulled
      nothing (silent no-op). Initialize it to ( "master" ).

    - pkg_git_diff_and_merge_branch_upstream: passed the bare remote
      'github-<proj>' instead of 'github-<proj>/master', so 'refs/remotes/...'
      was not a branch ref and the diff check silently no-oped. Pass the
      '/master' ref (matches the arraybolt3 / bot siblings and the previously
      commented intent).

    - pkg_git_diff_and_merge_branch: with the ref fixed, the merge dispatch had
      no case for the upstream value and fell through to 'die'. Add an upstream
      branch that verify-commits the tip (aborts under errexit on a bad/missing
      signature) then merges --no-ff, the same trusted-signed-source policy as
      the arraybolt3 branch. Also fix SC2124: 'origin_branch="$@"' -> "${1}".

