commit 76f8b5d16251e06b4873136593d72983ab5106a9
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 11:44:32 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: add R-010 'no-strict' waiver for sourced-only scripts

    R-010 requires the strict-mode block on every script, but a sourced-only
    fragment (an '/etc/profile.d/*.sh' login-shell fragment, a '.bashrc.d'
    snippet) must NOT set 'set -o errexit'/'nounset' at top level -- it would
    leak into and could kill the sourcing interactive shell. Such fragments do
    not use the was_executed()/was_sourced() guard that the existing skip
    detects.

    Add a '## style-ok: no-strict' whole-file waiver, mirroring the existing
    no-has / no-safe-rm escape hatches. Opt-in only: a file without the marker
    is unaffected, so existing enforcement does not change.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

commit fe6a25aebed679f4fca2fe5aeb50e5d89f9d4534
Author: claude (dev22 c20093f1-1b30-4397-87b6-9586321c87df) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed Jul 1 06:05:25 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: R-010 skip fully-guarded source-able scripts

    R-010 requires six strict-mode lines anchored at column 0 in the top 100
    lines. A source-able script (executed AND sourced for code reuse, e.g.
    usr/bin/update-torbrowser sourced by dist-installer-gui, or a pure
    helper-script .bsh library) must NOT enable strict-mode at top level:
    'set -o errexit'/'nounset' and 'shopt -s inherit_errexit' would leak into
    the sourcing shell. Such scripts therefore keep ZERO column-0 strict lines
    and guard the block behind the helper-scripts was_executed()/was_sourced()
    runtime check, indented out of reach of R-010's column-anchored regex.
    R-010 was thus unsatisfiable by any such file (check_runtime.bsh, a
    sanctioned upstream library, scores 0/6 too).

    Skip R-010 for exactly that shape: fully guarded (count 0) AND the
    was_executed()/was_sourced() guard present. The count==0 predicate is the
    correctness invariant, not a heuristic: a clean source-able script has no
    top-level strict lines at all. A partial top-level block (count 1..5, e.g.
    a standalone that uses was_sourced() only to REFUSE sourcing) is NOT a
    clean source-able script and stays subject to the count check, so its
    coverage is unchanged. This script itself keeps its own count-6 column-0
    block and so is never skipped despite naming the tokens in the detector.
    Emits a note when skipping, so the skip is visible rather than silent.

    Differential sweep over 1501 shell files in the tree: the only outcome
    changes are FAIL->skip for the 16 genuinely source-able count-0 scripts;
    no standalone or partial-block script changed behavior.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_018bezwAzE9uxSX1xrH7okFV

