    dm-packaging-helper-script: add pkg_git_push_atomic_unsigned

    Add an AI-model push target. The normal pkg_git_push_atomic is unchanged
    and stays secure-by-default (signs/verifies, and via genmkfile git-tag-push
    requires a signed tag at each branch tip). The AI model has no signing key
    yet, and its work-in-progress commits are untagged, so it needs an explicit
    opt-out: pkg_git_push_atomic_unsigned pushes the package branches directly
    with 'git push --atomic' -- no signature verification and no tag-at-tip
    requirement.

    Pushes are non-force (a diverged remote is rejected, not clobbered) and
    limited to the locally-configured remotes; scope to one mirror with e.g.
    'DM_PUSH_REMOTES_UNIVERSE=org-ai-assisted'. The derivative-maker meta-repo
    is skipped.

