Author: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 22 11:50:41 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: harden --staged mode after AI review

    Codex + a fresh-eyes pass flagged staged-mode gaps:
    - staged content checks read the working-tree copy, not the staged
      blob, so a file staged then re-edited was checked in its working-tree
      state silently. Now warn_staged_worktree_skew emits a per-file note
      when a checked path has unstaged changes (re-stage to verify the exact
      committed blob); suppressed under --all, where the working tree is the
      recorded set.
    - --message-file is now validated to exist (exit 2) instead of failing
      later with a raw cat/head error.
    Docstring tightened so the strict-mode block stays within the head-100
    R-010 window.

commit acdf0b479b827051f79cf83db2234e1cca085699
Author: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 22 11:15:05 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: add --staged mode for the Claude commit-gate hook

    Add a --staged [--all] [--message-file F] mode that checks the staged
    index instead of a commit range (pre-commit semantics), reusing every
    existing file-content check. The R-001 commit-message and changelog
    trailer checks run when a --message-file is supplied; without one they
    are skipped (push and CI still enforce them on the real commit-range).
    --staged and --per-commit are mutually exclusive.

    Consumed by the Claude Code commit-gate hook (dist-ai-config
    claude/hooks/dmf-gate.py), which runs this gate before every git commit
    so the developer-meta-files static checks apply to all repos by default,
    without per-repo .git/hooks wiring.

commit ecdf884e5b35ca25ed10db0fa9d94c9e16337faf
Author: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 22 09:05:18 2026 -0400

    pre-push-static: enforce genmkfile-owned debian/changelog (no hand-edit)

    debian/changelog is auto-generated by genmkfile; hand-editing it
    fights the tooling and the project's versioning convention. Add a
    commit-range check to the static gate: a commit that modifies
    debian/changelog passes only when it is a genmkfile auto-bump
    (exact 'bumped changelog version' subject and a changelog-family-only
    diff: debian/changelog and/or changelog.upstream) or carries a
    mandatory 'Changelog-manual-ok: <reason>' override trailer.

    Hard fail, consistent with the other gate checks; CI mirrors it.
    The check runs once over base..HEAD (like the ASCII commit-message
    check), inspecting each commit's diff and message individually so an
    auto-bump commit and a feature commit in the same range are judged
    on their own merits. Documented in the script header, AGENTS.md, and
    the pre-push checklist.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
