commit 96b81ee0cae3c699f2227111f3538cf69664713c
Author: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 18 07:57:43 2026 -0400

    launch-systemd-container: mask tmp.mount so docker cp to /tmp works

    systemd >= 256 mounts a tmpfs over /tmp by default (tmp.mount). Inside a
    container that shadows anything docker cp writes to /tmp: the copy lands
    in the lower directory while the running system sees the empty tmpfs, so
    copied files silently vanish. Mask tmp.mount so /tmp stays a plain
    directory on the container filesystem; docker cp to /tmp then works and
    persists, matching pre-256 behaviour.

    Verified against a throwaway build of the edited Dockerfile: /tmp is no
    longer a separate mount, tmp.mount is masked, docker cp to /tmp is
    visible from exec, and systemctl is-system-running stays 'running' with
    no failed units.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

