Author: claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue Jun 2 13:44:11 2026 -0400

    Exempt branch-switch targets from on-master pre-flight guard

    pkg_git_check_current_branch runs before every target and returns
    non-zero for any repo not on master. Under errexit this aborts the
    whole run, so the branch-switching commands (pkg_git_branch_checkout_*
    and pkg_git_branch_trixie) could never execute when a repo was left
    on a non-master branch (e.g. detached HEAD) - a catch-22, since their
    entire purpose is to put the repo back on master.

    Add pkg_git_target_is_branch_switch and skip the pre-flight guard for
    those targets in both batch and no-batch modes.

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

