commit 62c7c823887d92f0334e165f101e39381f40dbe6
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 09:52:15 2026 +0000

    github-policy: required_signatures on PERSON with User-actor bypass; OrgAdmin bypass on SOURCE

    Unblocks pushes against repos with unsigned historical commits
    without dropping the required_signatures rule entirely.

    SOURCE (Kicksecure / Whonix):
      rule stays on. Bypass changed from [] -> [OrganizationAdmin]
      (same shape MIRROR already uses), so the org owner can push
      unsigned commits while non-admin contributors are still blocked.

    PERSON (adrelanos personal mirror):
      rule stays on. Bypass is computed at --apply time from
      GET /users/{login} -> [{actor_id: <user_id>, actor_type: "User",
      bypass_mode: "always"}]. User-owned repos have no
      OrganizationAdmin equivalent, but actor_type=User on a
      repo-level ruleset is the repo-owner-bypass equivalent. The
      maintainer can keep pushing unsigned commits to their own
      mirror repos while non-admin collaborators with write access
      remain bound by the rule.

    BOT (assisted-by-ai and peers):
      no required_signatures (AI-assisted pushes carry no verifiable
      GPG key for the bot identity, so the rule would block every
      legitimate push). Bypass stays as []: the remaining rules
      (deletion, non_fast_forward) protect the bot from accidental
      force-push / branch deletion on its own repos. Granting a User
      bypass on BOT would defeat that protection.

    MIRROR (org-ai-assisted): unchanged.

    Live-tested:
      GET /users/adrelanos -> HTTP 200, user_id=1985040.
      Generated PERSON body has the [User: 1985040] bypass + the
      3-rule list including required_signatures; generated BOT body
      has [] bypass + the 2-rule list. dm-github-personal-policy
      adrelanos --dry-run iterates all 41 repos and prints the
      planned upserts.

    Files:
    - usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/github-policy-data.bsh:
      - POLICY_RULESET_BYPASS_SOURCE: [] -> [OrganizationAdmin].
      - POLICY_RULESET_RULES_PERSON: unchanged (3 rules including
        required_signatures).
      - Doc blocks rewritten to cover all four roles (SOURCE,
        MIRROR, PERSON, BOT) and clarify that bypass_mode: "always"
        exempts the actor from every rule, not just history.
    - usr/bin/dm-github-personal-policy:
      - case "${target_kind}": person resolves user_id via
        GET /users/{login} and builds [{User, target_user_id,
        always}]; bot hardcodes []; unexpected kind dies.
    - agents/github-policy-canonical-vs-mirror.md: summary table
      + items 2-3 in "Net deliberate diffs" rewritten to match.
    - agents/pre-push-static.sh: anchor style-ok waiver regex
      (extended-regex with leading/trailing word boundary) so
      no-has-typo cannot satisfy a no-has waiver. Applies to both
      the no-has and no-safe-rm waivers.
    - ci/tests/test_ruleset_body_rules_dispatch.sh: contract pin
      for PERSON kept at 3 rules including required_signatures
      (this PR pins the post-rebase contract).

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01GUPFaPsw673d33HL5jbCbW

commit 5d28fb077f6f9b791ba9ab7071ca00cf38a5b255
Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu May 28 05:52:01 2026 -0400

    pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie: actionable divergence diagnostic (#123)

    ## Why

    When `pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie`'s ancestry check fails, the
    old `die` message was just:

    ```
    qubes-template-whonix: pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie 'trixie' has commits not on master; ff-only sync would fail - reconcile manually
    ```

    That leaves the operator to:
    1. Dig out the divergent SHAs.
    2. Count the unique commits.
    3. Decide whether the divergence is content-real or just stranded
    merge-commit history.
    4. Invent the reset command.

    Common case in practice after the May-25 strategy flip (`aef7153` _
    develop on master, mirror tag to trixie): some trixie tips are
    content-identical merge commits like `Merge branch 'master' into
    trixie`, so `git diff master trixie` is empty but ancestry-check
    correctly fails. The user just needs to reset trixie; the message should
    tell them so.

    ## After

    ```
    qubes-template-whonix: pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie 'trixie' (2a123a95ce02) has 2 commit(s) not on master (c59605209ad2); ff-only sync would fail. Trees identical: yes (only merge-commit history differs; reset is content-safe). To reconcile: git switch trixie && git reset --hard c59605209ad2... && git push --force-with-lease origin trixie && git switch master
    ```

    If trees actually differ (real work on trixie), the message says so and
    the operator knows a hard reset would lose work.

    ## Scope

    Same control flow, same exit code. Only the failure message changes. No
    behavior change on the success path.

    ## Test plan

    - [x] `bash -n usr/bin/dm-packaging-helper-script` passes.
    - [x] Ran the new diagnostic snippet against a real divergent
    qubes-template-whonix tree _ produces the expected output (`ahead by:
    2`, `trees identical: yes`).

    ---
    _Generated by [Claude
    Code](https://claude.ai/code/session_01GnpfnyzLETPpPz1G6smsRV)_

