    git-helpers.bsh: delegate atomic push to genmkfile git-tag-push

    Collapse internal_git_push_atomic_all_remotes to a per-repo
    filter (DM_PUSH_BRANCHES_UNIVERSE + DM_PUSH_REMOTES_UNIVERSE
    intersected with refs that exist locally) + an exec of
    'genmkfile git-tag-push' with make_git_push_branches /
    make_git_push_remotes set in the call's environment.

    All push mechanics (atomic --porcelain, parallel per remote,
    strict missing-branch / missing-tag / missing-remote errors,
    skip-already-pushed cache) now live in genmkfile's
    make_git_tag_push. See org-ai-assisted/genmkfile#23.

    Signed-release trust boundary stays in dmf: internal_git_verify_ref
    (only ref-verification helper restored; the rest stay removed
    since genmkfile owns push mechanics) is called for every branch
    tip + dedup'd tip tag before delegating, covering both the
    dm-push direct path and the branch tips that dm-packaging-
    helper-script's HEAD-only pre-verify misses.

    Removed (no callers outside this file; grep clean across dmf,
    derivative-maker, helper-scripts):
      - internal_git_diff / internal_git_diff_local / internal_git_diff_remote
      - internal_git_tags_at_branch_tips
      - internal_git_verify_and_push_to_remote
      - internal_git_compute_refspecs_for_remote
      - internal_git_verify_refspecs
      - internal_git_push_refspecs

    Added:
      - DM_PUSH_BRANCHES_UNIVERSE constant ('main master trixie')

    Net: git-helpers.bsh shrinks from 325 lines to ~105.

    dm-packaging-helper-script: exports
    make_git_tag_push_cache_dir="${derivative_binary_dir}/git-tag-push-cache"
    once at script init. Every dm-push / pkg_git_push_atomic
    invocation in a run inherits the env var and opts in to
    genmkfile's skip-already-pushed cache.

    github-org-push: XXX comment marking 'git push --tags' as
    intentionally not migrated (bulk push-all-tags semantics don't
    fit the per-tag cache; intentional for mass-mirror-to-fork).

    Unchanged public surface: internal_git_push_atomic_all_remotes
    (called by dm-push + pkg_git_push_atomic) and
    internal_git_known_push_remotes stay in place with same
    signatures.

