    dm-github-org-policy: comment out paid-plan-only and App-only audit blocks

    Two audit subsections never returned data under our actual setup
    (Free-plan org, classic PAT auth):

    - 'existing rulesets named ...' walks GET /orgs/{org}/rulesets,
      which 403s on Free with body "Upgrade to GitHub Team to enable
      this feature." Apply uses repo-level rulesets (Free-compatible)
      via policy_upsert_repo_ruleset, so this listing block carries
      no Free-plan operational value.

    - 'fine-grained PAT activity:' walks two GitHub-App-only endpoints
      (personal-access-token-requests + personal-access-tokens).
      Classic and fine-grained PATs are rejected regardless of scope
      with HTTP 404 + empty x-accepted-oauth-scopes. The org's
      PAT-restriction policy toggle does not change this.
      dm-github-org-policy is entirely PAT-authenticated via
      ghorg_api, so the block could not return data.

    Both blocks are commented out (not deleted) in the established
    'PAID PLAN ONLY' style of apply_code_security_config(): re-enable
    by uncommenting if either constraint changes (plan upgrade, or
    addition of an App-token code path). Unused local var
    declarations (ruleset_body, ruleset_name, ids, id, pending,
    approved) removed alongside.

