commit 21256926dcc1f14abffcbd962ceb7b81d8314976
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed May 27 11:02:59 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: clearer audit hints + per-repo dependabot.yml display

    Three small audit-output fixes surfaced while running --audit
    against a Free-plan org with a fully-scoped classic PAT:

    1. 'rulesets list: HTTP 403' was reported as '(token may lack
       admin:org)' when the actual cause is plan-gating: org-level
       rulesets are GitHub Team+ only. Free-plan orgs always get
       403 here regardless of scope. The script itself documents
       this (line 80-84: "PAID PLAN ONLY"); the audit hint did not.
       Now reads '(paid plan only / token may lack admin:org)'.

    2. 'approved tokens endpoint: HTTP 404' was reported as
       '(token may lack admin:org)' when the cause is more often
       that the org has not enabled the PAT restriction policy.
       Mirrors the wording of the parallel 'requests endpoint'
       hint two cases above. Now reads '(token may lack admin:org
       / PAT restriction policy not enforced)'.

    3. dependabot.yml audit listed only the missing repos and a
       have/missing summary at the end. Useful for spotting which
       repos lack the file, but not for confirming the ones that
       should have it actually do. Now emits 'yes:' / 'no:'
       per repo and a 'summary:' line. Propagating dependabot.yml
       to every repo is not the goal - many repos (apt sources,
       meta-packages, base files, ...) have no language deps and
       would just produce empty Dependabot runs - so the audit's
       value is visibility, not a checklist of TODOs.

