commit aeef1e363639da4d42c25b3b10a59c8ea19c388a
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 26 16:56:44 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: use 'git merge --no-ff' for branch merges

    sq-git authenticates a chain by walking from a trust root and
    validating each commit against openpgp-policy.toml. Drive-by
    contributors (Aaron's trixie branch, AI mirror branches) are
    deliberately NOT in the policy file. The sanctioned way to land
    their work is a '--no-ff' merge: the maintainer-signed merge
    commit authenticates the unsigned commits below it.

    Plain 'git merge' fast-forwards when possible, leaving drive-by
    commits on the first-parent chain with no authorizing merge
    commit. sq-git log then refuses them and the chain breaks.

    'pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie' keeps '--ff-only'
    intentionally: 'trixie' there is a strict mirror of master and
    must not diverge.

