    R-090: add 'style-ok: no-has' script-wide waiver (#117)

    R-090 already had a hard-coded R-093 carve-out for two specific scripts that run before helper-scripts is reachable, but other bootstrap-time scripts in the same situation had no escape hatch except switching to a fixed-path test. Mirror the existing R-120 '## style-ok: no-safe-rm' waiver: '## style-ok: no-has' anywhere in a script disables R-090 for that file. bash-style-guide.md documents both the waiver and the preferred alternative (path test where the install location is stable), so the waiver stays the rare-case escape rather than the lazy default.

commit 255f5e1cdd8a38e4e1e55e23f2c66e3de9113c8c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 26 11:45:56 2026 +0000

    R-090: add 'style-ok: no-has' script-wide waiver

    R-090 already had an R-093 carve-out for two specific scripts
    (install-helper-scripts.sh, pre-push-static.sh) hard-coded into
    the gate, but other bootstrap-time scripts that run before
    helper-scripts is on the system had no escape hatch except a path
    test. Mirror the existing R-120 'style-ok: no-safe-rm' waiver
    shape: '## style-ok: no-has' anywhere in a script disables R-090
    for that file.

    Documentation in bash-style-guide.md now describes both the
    waiver and the preferred alternative (a fixed-path test like
    '[ -x /usr/sbin/foo ]') for binaries whose install location is
    stable, so the waiver remains the rare-case escape it's meant to
    be rather than the easy default.

