commit d209e34754454d769f84fc8e0301700e0a2a96f8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 25 18:44:30 2026 +0000

    launch-systemd-container action + install-deps install-self-mode

    * .github/actions/launch-systemd-container/
        New composite action: builds a Debian-based docker image
        with systemd as PID 1 (via a sibling Dockerfile + ARG IMAGE /
        ARG APT_BOOTSTRAP_PACKAGES) and starts it detached +
        --privileged so subsequent workflow steps `docker exec`
        against a real init. Caller runs on a host runner without
        the `container:` directive. /tmp is mounted with the `exec`
        flag explicitly so equivs-build / dpkg-buildpackage / pip
        wheels can exec generated scripts from mktemp dirs (Docker's
        --tmpfs default is noexec).

    * .github/actions/install-deps/
        New install-self-mode input (install | deb-icup). 'install'
        is the previous file-copy install via genmkfile; 'deb-icup'
        builds and apt-installs the real .deb so the postinst runs
        (required by consumers that rely on config-package-dev
        displace / divert, e.g. dist-encrypted). Body moves to
        install-self.sh (sibling of install-genmkfile.sh /
        install-helper-scripts.sh).

        Drop the dead GENMKFILE_DEBUG=1 prefix from all three
        install-* scripts: it was placed before `sudo`, which then
        stripped it from the env passed to genmkfile, so debug
        output was never produced.

