commit aef7153268a9a2c89a5fdd8ff33cb326f9de93de
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 25 17:53:03 2026 +0000

    Develop qubes-template-(kicksecure|whonix) on master, mirror tag to trixie + push unification + cleanup sweep

    Flip the qubes-template-(kicksecure|whonix) workflow: develop on
    master locally, mirror the master tag onto trixie automatically.
    Unify the push path so dm-push and the batch flow both go through
    one shared, atomic-per-remote helper. Plus a substantial cleanup
    sweep (FIXMEs, TODOs, XXX markers, R-010 conformance) that landed
    on the same branch during PR life.

    WHY (qubes-template flip)

    These two special repos were being developed on trixie locally
    even though their GitHub default branch is master. derivative-
    maker pinned the submodule SHA at trixie tip, but its CI clones
    with --shallow-submodules: a shallow clone of master does not
    auto-follow tags pointing at a non-default-branch tip, and a
    follow-up 'git fetch <SHA>' doesn't auto-follow tags either.
    Result: git_sanity_test flagged the submodule as 'Untagged commit'
    even though the tag existed on the remote.

    Working on master instead, then mirroring the tag onto trixie,
    lands the parent-pinned SHA on the submodule's default branch tip
    - so the shallow clone always fetches the corresponding tag.

    WORKFLOW CHANGE (qubes-template-(kicksecure|whonix))

    - Local dev branch is now master (was trixie).
    - pkg_git_sign_tags signs HEAD on master, then
      pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie fast-forwards trixie onto
      master, signs trixie's new tip, and returns to master. Idem-
      potent; --ff-only so divergent trixie surfaces to the operator
      rather than producing a merge commit. A read-only
      'git merge-base --is-ancestor' runs before the destructive ops
      so divergence is caught in dry-run too.
    - dm-qubes-templates-official-build-commands is one loop: per
      template repo, switch to master, dm-quickgittagsign (signs
      master AND mirrors to trixie), dm-push.

    PUSH UNIFICATION (all repos)

    - New git-helpers.bsh library:
      * internal_git_known_push_remotes - enumerates push remotes
        (github-kicksecure, github-whonix, adrelanos, $DM_GITHUB_
        MIRROR) that exist locally. Replaces the per-project
        batch_current_package_remote_list subset for the push path.
      * internal_git_verify_ref - per-ref signature check
        (verify-commit for branches, verify-tag for tags).
      * Per-remote three-phase helper:
        internal_git_compute_refspecs_for_remote ->
        internal_git_verify_refspecs -> internal_git_push_refspecs.
        Composed by internal_git_verify_and_push_to_remote.
      * internal_git_push_atomic_all_remotes - parallel-per-remote
        driver, one --atomic --porcelain push per remote so branches
        + tip tags succeed or fail together.
      * Internal helpers take a caller-named output array (nameref)
        instead of stdout, so the function bodies run in the caller's
        shell and errexit propagates directly without process-
        substitution swallowing the exit status.
    - dm-push is now a ~30-line thin wrapper over
      internal_git_push_atomic_all_remotes.
    - dm-packaging-helper-script: pkg_git_push_remotes +
      pkg_git_push_tags collapsed into one pkg_git_push_atomic.
      Dry-run handled at this consumer level (one WOULD line) so the
      shared library stays a pure 'actually push' helper.
    - Pushed branches: main, master, trixie (existing-only).
      bookworm is intentionally not in the list - drop per operator
      decision.
    - Canonical push-remote universe hoisted to a new
      DM_PUSH_REMOTES_UNIVERSE readonly array near the top of
      git-helpers.bsh; internal_git_known_push_remotes iterates the
      constant. set_batch_current_package_remote_list docstring
      rewritten to acknowledge it's intentionally narrower (per-
      package fetch list, project-aware).

    CLEANUP SWEEP (incidental but in scope)

    - Interactive 'read -r _' fallbacks in internal_git_diff_local /
      _remote guarded with [ -t 0 ] so CI / cron / piped callers see
      the warning but don't block on stdin.

    - 4 FIXMEs resolved across dm-packaging-helper-script and
      github-org-*:
      * GHORG_MOCK switched from 0/1 to 'true'/'false' string boolean
        per R-053 (2 source call sites + 18 ci/tests + 2 docs).
      * Canonical dependabot.yml path hoisted to a global
        canonical_dependabot_yml constant; deduplicated.
      * parse_args docstring fixed (stale 'declared near the bottom'
        claim replaced with 'initializes and writes the parsed_*
        globals listed below').
      * '--repo implies --no-batch' inference moved from main() into
        parse_args() so all flag-shape logic lives in one place.

    - 6 TODOs resolved:
      * dm-check-mirrors: drop commented-out single-mirror debug
        block and stale 'TODO: --max-time' (already set on the per-
        mirror scurl).
      * Drop a 9-line commented-out 'TODO: delete /tmp/list-of-
        packages' fallback in pkg_packaging_files_diff.
      * Default '*) die 1 ...' arm in set_batch_context_from_pwd so a
        new entry in repo_is_special that forgets a project mapping
        fails loud.
      * 'leading-space TODO' on extract_description_from_debian_
        control replaced with a Debian Policy 5.6.13 citation.
      * pkg_install_dependabot_yml: drop the redundant dependabot_
        yml_is_manual check (INSTALL semantic; the file-exists check
        handles all 'already present' cases).

    - 3 larger TODO refactors:
      * pkg_update_consumer_workflows: replace the 11-entry hardcoded
        consumer-wrapper list with a nullglob scan of
        ${canonical_workflows_dir}/*.yml.
      * Sweep trailing 'true' to 'return 0' at function tails
        (37 sites).
      * Hoist canonical push-remote universe (see PUSH UNIFICATION).

    - 2 XXX markers resolved:
      * Drop dead 3-line SourceForge upload template stub in
        dm-upload-repository.
      * dm-packaging-helper-script: the local nothing_to_commit() was
        byte-identical to helper-scripts/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/
        git.sh; source git.sh and delete the local copy.

    - R-010 compliance: dm-check-mirrors had only 5/6 strict-mode
      lines; add 'shopt -s shift_verbose'.

    OUT-OF-SCOPE FIXES TO KEEP CI GREEN

    - dm-qubes-templates-official-build-commands: missing 'shopt -s
      shift_verbose' added (R-010).
    - dm-tor-update-repository: file-level '# shellcheck disable=
      SC2317' for the intentional dead code below the early 'exit 0'
      TODO stub.

    CODERABBIT REVIEW

    Three review passes; all valid findings folded in:
    - git tag --points-at stray '--' removed in both dm-push and
      dm-packaging-helper-script.
    - Ancestry check added to dry-run path of
      pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie so divergent trixie surfaces
      even when dry_run_or_run skips the destructive ops.
    - pkg_git_qubes_template_sync_trixie destructive ops grouped
      under a single dry-run guard.
    - declare -A switched to local -A inside
      internal_git_push_atomic_all_remotes for clearer intent.

