commit 40d2cd174a903312e5a0b93dc0b3a4f1ae8a5333
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 18:00:37 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: cat-to-file concat via tee --append (not append)

    The earlier conversion of all tee calls to append/overwrite forced
    file-to-file concatenation through `append FILE "$(<SRC)"`, which:

    - relies on the bash-arcane $(<file) form;
    - loads file content into argv (memory + no-NUL-byte limits);
    - strips trailing newlines.

    `append` is naturally string-content. File-to-file concat is a
    different operation. Revert the 3 cat-pipe sites to use the natural
    cat | tee --append pattern, with `dry_run_or_run` wrapping `tee` for
    dry-run coverage. The hardened dry_run_or_run drains piped stdin on
    dry-run so large-file cat won't SIGPIPE under errexit+pipefail
    (verified with a 143MB file).

    Affected:
    - pkg_readme_creator_do: template -> readme
    - pkg_descr_merger: per-package mediawiki -> merged
    - pkg_descr_merge_all: merged -> allmerged

