commit 0b93c546c3161f9424502e153963c502f7fdc6ca
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 18:00:37 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: parse_args + --repo, full dry-run via append/overwrite

    Two user-reported bugs and an end-to-end dry-run coverage pass.

    Bug fixes:

    - shift_verbose ("shift count out of range") leaked to stderr on any
      invocation without a function-name positional. `shift || true` only
      swallows the exit code; replaced with a $# guard so shift only runs
      when there's something to shift.
    - `--no-batch --repo NAME` without a function name silently fell
      through to the list-functions-and-exit-0 path (--repo consumed the
      intended function name as its NAME value). Now fails fast with a
      clear "missing function name" error and shows the correct syntax.

    main()/parse_args restructure:

    - parse_args() extracted as a pure parser writing parsed_* globals;
      flag-shape knowledge in one place.
    - Mode validation hoisted to a standalone early check
      ([ -z parsed_mode ] && [ parsed_target != '' ] -> fatal). Bare
      invocation with no flags and no target still lists.
    - --repo selects a single repo by name; implies --no-batch and is
      rejected with --batch.
    - --no-batch + --repo resolution + cd via resolve_repo_path; flat
      guard-clauses, defensive else for unexpected parsed_mode.

    Dry-run coverage (--dry-run / batch_meta_dry_run='y'):

    Phase 1 - wrapped every mechanical git mutation: pkg_git_reset,
    pkg_git_diff_and_commit, pkg_git_diff_and_merge_branch, all
    pkg_git_branch_*, pkg_git_remotes_add (16 sites), pkg_compat_delete,
    git_reset_changelog_upstream, all pkg_git_commit_*, pkg_git_manpages,
    pkg_git_debinstfile, pkg_install_*, pkg_copy_contributing_file,
    pkg_update_if_exists, pkg_readme_creator_commit,
    pkg_claude_md_pointer_create, debian_watch_file_create.

    Phase 3 - wrapped fetch / status / diff per user direction. mkdir in
    prepare_system kept live.

    dry_run_or_run hardened: WOULD message goes to stderr (survives
    >/dev/null on stdout); piped stdin is drained on dry-run so upstream
    producers don't SIGPIPE under errexit+pipefail.

    tee migration to append/overwrite from helper-scripts:

    All tee/tee --append pipelines replaced with append/overwrite calls
    through dry_run_or_run. Patterns:

    - printf '%s\n' "X" | tee --append -- "F"   ->   append "F" "X"
    - printf '%s\n' '' | tee --append -- "F"    ->   append "F" $'\n'
    - cat -- "SRC" | tee --append -- "DST"      ->   append "DST" "$(<"SRC")"
    - printf '...' | tee -- "F"                 ->   overwrite "F" "..."

    All safe-rm sites wrapped too. Function-level early-returns dropped
    where per-statement wrapping makes them redundant.

    check_prerequisites: argless again (no main() recursion), structural
    checks only. Added `has append` and `has overwrite`.

    repo_is_special expanded: live-build, grml-debootstrap,
    grml-debootstraptest now part of the iterated set; pick up the same
    tag-and-push flow as qubes-template-*, Whonix-Installer, Whonix-Starter.

    run_batch collapsed to two pushd + set_batch_context_from_pwd +
    run_batch_command + popd loops (packages first, then top-level
    specials, derivative-maker last).

    run_batch_command: dropped inner pushd/popd; caller owns cwd.

    set_batch_context_from_pwd: parameter expansion instead of
    basename/dirname subshells (~50% faster per call).

