commit e3e2f16f229c34d21227c6a08d95b764f6d58ef8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 19 09:42:58 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: mandatory --batch/--no-batch, single-repo --repo, refactor

    Batch mode and --no-batch previously took divergent paths. Batch set
    batch_current_project_name / website / changelog / path / remote_list
    per iteration; --no-batch only set batch_current_package_reponame from
    $(basename "$PWD") and called the target directly. Functions that read
    the other globals silently saw empty/garbage state in --no-batch.
    run_batch itself had ~70 lines split between an outer if/elif loop for
    packages/{kicksecure,whonix}/* and five hardcoded special-case blocks
    restating the same assignments. check_prerequisites recursively called
    main --batch pkg_git_check_current_branch as a pre-flight, forcing a
    full-batch pre-flight even under --no-batch.

    Changes:

    - parse_args(): new pure parser. Writes parsed_mode, parsed_repo,
      parsed_target, parsed_args, parsed_dry_run. Single source of truth
      for flag-shape knowledge.
    - main(): calls parse_args, resolves --repo, dispatches via explicit
      if/elif/else: --no-batch runs pre-flight + user-target on the single
      repo with one post-hook pass; --batch runs pre-flight via run_batch
      then user-target dispatch. else = defensive "missing mode" error.
    - check_prerequisites: argless again, structural checks only. No more
      main() recursion, no forwarding loop.
    - set_batch_context_from_pwd(): new helper that derives all
      batch_current_* from PWD. derivative-maker meta-repo handled
      explicitly; repo_is_special covers the top-level non-package
      submodules (qubes-template-{ks,wx}, Whonix-{Installer,Starter}, plus
      live-build, grml-debootstrap, grml-debootstraptest); regular packages
      detected via parent-dir match. Fail-fast on unrecognized.
    - repo_is_special: expanded from 4 to 7 entries. live-build /
      grml-debootstrap / grml-debootstraptest were not iterated by run_batch
      before this PR; they are now, picking up the same tag-and-push flow
      the other special-cases follow.
    - run_batch(): collapsed to two pushd + set_batch_context_from_pwd +
      run_batch_command + popd loops (regular packages first via
      packages/*/* glob, then top-level specials, derivative-maker last
      so per-package writes have run before pkg_git_submodule_file_writer
      re-runs on the meta-repo).
    - run_batch_command: dropped inner pushd/popd. Caller owns cwd, set
      via set_batch_context_from_pwd; both --batch and --no-batch paths
      enter the target repo before invoking.
    - resolve_repo_path(): new helper for --repo NAME. Tries
      derivative-maker root, qubes/, windows/, packages/kicksecure/,
      packages/whonix/ in that order. Rejects names containing '/' or
      starting with '.' as path-traversal guards.
    - --repo implies --no-batch; --batch + --repo is rejected with a clear
      error. Mutex check for --batch / --no-batch deduplicated by
      collapsing the case arms via mode="${1#--}".

    In-tree caller audit: dm-quickgittagsign already passes --no-batch.
    check_prerequisites updated. Wiki-doc references (out-of-tree backups)
    still show the no-flag form; deferred to a separate doc update.

    Side-note: set_batch_context_from_pwd uses parameter expansion
    (${pwd_abs##*/}, ${pwd_abs%/*}) instead of basename/dirname subshells;
    ~50% faster per call.

