commit 6a5114011382ae1f900a30ff992669eb24a806a0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 18 23:09:15 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: collapse run_batch via set_batch_context_from_pwd

    run_batch had ~70 lines split between an outer if/elif loop for the
    regular packages/{kicksecure,whonix}/* iteration and five hardcoded
    special-case blocks at the tail. Every block restated the same
    batch_current_* assignments that set_batch_context_from_pwd already
    derives from PWD.

    Collapse to two loops: one globbing packages/*/* (project derived from
    parent dir), one over an explicit list of top-level repos (special-cases
    recognized via repo_is_special / explicit derivative-maker case).
    Iteration order preserved (regular packages first, derivative-maker
    last so per-package writes have run before pkg_git_submodule_file_writer
    re-runs over the meta-repo).

    run_batch_command: drop the inner pushd/popd. Caller now owns cwd
    (--batch path pushd's per iteration; --no-batch path is already in the
    target repo when main() invokes it after set_batch_context_from_pwd).

    Side-effect: batch mode now iterates live-build, grml-debootstrap,
    grml-debootstraptest. These are in repo_is_special (added in #110) and
    follow the same tag-and-push flow as the other special-cases; batch
    runs now apply auto-sign / version-bump-check to them too.

