commit c335685c00eee25efed529b752d4856299e1c6d5
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 18 15:05:51 2026 +0000

    shellcheck source paths: standardize on relative submodule-friendly paths

    Apply the convention the FIXME in dm-github-org-metadata-sync
    documented. The same library file is shipped both at /usr/libexec/...
    (installed) and at the source tree path of the in-tree checkout;
    absolute 'source=' directives followed the installed copy, which can
    drift from the source tree under review. Relative directives point
    at the source tree the developer is actually editing.

    Conventions used:
    - usr/bin/<script>  -> developer-meta-files self-libs:
        # shellcheck source=../libexec/developer-meta-files/<lib>.bsh
    - usr/bin/<script>  -> helper-scripts (submodule layout):
        # shellcheck source=../../../helper-scripts/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/<file>
    - usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/<lib>.bsh -> helper-scripts:
        # shellcheck source=../../../../helper-scripts/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/<file>
    - ci/<script> at depth 1:
        # shellcheck source=../usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/<lib>
        # shellcheck source=../../helper-scripts/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/<file>
    - ci/tests/<script> at depth 2:
        # shellcheck source=../../usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/<lib>
        # shellcheck source=../../../helper-scripts/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/<file>

    These resolve against the source tree when a developer checks out
    the derivative-maker submodule layout (the assumed canonical context
    per the FIXME). Standalone shellcheck on a bare developer-meta-files
    checkout falls back to SC1091 ('not found') for the helper-scripts
    paths, which is acceptable - the in-tree copy of the library shipped
    alongside is what matters for accurate linting.

commit c4342b411ae7fb4eb8366ce4a90ad9a7e4342bfb
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 18 15:03:34 2026 +0000

    pre-push-static.sh: catch 'bash extensionless-script' and bare 'rm'

    R-102 check: extend the regex to also match invocations of an
    extensionless script through the bash/sh interpreter ('bash my-tool',
    'sh ./my-tool'), while filtering known-good 'bash -c' / 'sh -x' /
    similar flag patterns. The previous regex only matched the
    *.sh / *.bsh / *.bash extensions.

    R-120 check: extend the rm regex with a third alternative
    ('^[[:space:]]*rm$') so a single-token 'rm' line at the start of
    the file is no longer missed.

    git-helpers.bsh: this file is now in the gate's changed-files set
    (touched by an earlier R-053 commit on this branch), so add the
    canonical R-010 strict-mode block + exec bit to match
    github-policy-lib.bsh and github-org-lib.bsh.

commit 03816142c154c6fc8ce3f8bedc54a5bf3cc5adc9
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
