commit b57df9b1f612ede27bf8977e0c54ac81bfa6ac8a
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 17:42:17 2026 +0000

    dependabot.yml: drop docker block from canonical; add manual-opt-out

    The previous canonical at consumer-templates/.github/dependabot.yml
    carried both github-actions and docker package-ecosystem blocks on
    the documented theory that the docker block was a "harmless no-op"
    in repos without a /Dockerfile. That theory was wrong: the
    dependabot-action errors with `dependency_file_not_found` and
    aborts the whole job - including the github-actions ecosystem run
    that shares it - so every consumer using the canonical lost its
    github-actions Dependabot coverage too.

    Canonical is now github-actions only. Docker-bearing repos
    (derivative-maker at docker/Dockerfile, helper-scripts at
    .clusterfuzzlite/Dockerfile) opt out of byte-identical propagation
    via a "## propagation: manual" header marker and hand-maintain
    their own dependabot.yml with a correctly-pathed docker block.

    dm-packaging-helper-script: new dependabot_yml_is_manual helper;
    pkg_install_dependabot_yml and pkg_update_consumer_workflows now
    grep -q for the marker and skip the file when present.

    agents/github-actions-consumer-templates.md: replaces the
    "Unified canonical" subsection with "Canonical scope: github-
    actions only" plus a new "Per-repo manual dependabot.yml" section
    documenting the opt-out marker and the two current manually-
    maintained repos.

commit b0cc0fde709c5ff6da1a565b6082cf83cf50a9dd
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 17:37:53 2026 +0000

    drop pkg_verify_signed_commit/_and_tag wrappers; clean up pkg_git_sign_tags

    The two wrappers were thin shims around genmkfile targets that had
    identical semantics:

      pkg_verify_signed_commit       == genmkfile git-commit-verify
      pkg_verify_signed_commit_and_tag == genmkfile git-verify (+
                                          derivative-maker skip)

    The derivative-maker skip in the second wrapper was redundant -
    the only caller (pkg_git_push_remotes) is only reached after the
    outer-level functions skip derivative-maker. Inline the genmkfile
    calls at every site; drop both wrapper definitions and the dead
    commented-out pkg_resign_with_sq stub.

    pkg_git_sign_tags rewrite:
      - 3-step structure (was 4 announced as 1/4-3/4 with no 4/4),
        counting now matches the work
      - drop the noisy "<step> TODO" / "<step> done" pair per step;
        one log line per step is sufficient
      - use `genmkfile git-tag-verify` in step 2's gate instead of
        `genmkfile git-verify`; we already did the commit check in
        step 1, so re-running it inside the conditional was wasted
      - step 3's final `genmkfile git-verify` is the full sanity
        check (commit + tag), kept under dry_run_or_run so a dry-run
        pass doesn't trip on step 2's would-be (unfinished) sign

    Net: -29 lines including the deleted wrappers.

commit 2cad35717dde1428097f905301affd5f6a195774
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 16:57:02 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: add --dry-run

    New batch_meta_dry_run flag plus a dry_run_or_run helper that wraps
    every state-mutating command. In dry-run the helper logs

       [DRY-RUN] <reponame>: WOULD: <cmd args...>

    and returns 0 instead of running the command. Read-only commands
    (verifications, queries, parsers, sanity tests) are NOT wrapped -
    they always run so dry-run can surface policy violations
    (unsigned commit, missing tag, debian/control absent, etc.) before
    a real run.

    CLI: `--dry-run` as the first argument
      dm-packaging-helper-script --dry-run pkg_need_version_bump_and_pkg_build_and_reprepro_add

    Wrapped sites:
      - pkg_upstream_and_debian_changelog_bump: genmkfile deb-uachl-{bumpup-manual,bumpup-major,commit-changelog}
      - pkg_git_sign_tags: genmkfile git-tag-sign + the post-condition git-verify (the latter so dry-run can continue past this function instead of failing on a tag the mutation didn't create)
      - pkg_need_version_bump_and_pkg_build_and_reprepro_add: genmkfile deb-pkg / reprepro-remove / reprepro-add / deb-cleanup
      - pkg_only_build_all: genmkfile deb-pkg
      - pkg_only_reprepro_add: genmkfile reprepro-add

    Backgrounded `git push &` in pkg_git_push_remotes and
    pkg_git_push_tags can't be expressed through dry_run_or_run because
    the `&` is essential; both sites use an inline conditional that
    mirrors the helper's output format.

    For signed-tag creation, dry-run says "WOULD: genmkfile git-tag-sign"
    without predicting the exact target version - per the design
    discussion, prediction would require duplicating genmkfile's
    version-bump logic and the precision isn't worth the complexity.

