commit ea233b74bf808ff40d62610219509a597d4c8036
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 17 16:15:44 2026 +0000

    pkg_need_version_bump_show: drop redundant =""; grep --fixed-strings --

    Two micro-cleanups on the reprepro version extraction:

    1. The pre-assignment `source_line=""` / `reprepro_version=""` lines
       were redundant. The vars are declared in the function's `local`
       line at the top and assigned by the very next statement; nothing
       reads them in between.

    2. The literal-string filter is more correctly expressed as
       `grep --fixed-strings -- '|source:'`:
       - R-060: long flag.
