commit 858c2bcd61dce8cf5618ce221aa20d98fd2fca5f
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 16 21:45:47 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: integrate special repos into version-bump batch

    `pkg_need_version_bump_and_pkg_build_and_reprepro_add` previously
    early-returned on the four special (non-package) repos via
    `repo_skip_non_package`, so a special repo whose HEAD commit was
    signed but lacked a tag at HEAD was silently ignored by the
    batch "rebuild all that need it" entry point.

    Add a `repo_is_special` discriminator and dispatch on it inside the
    existing helpers so the same call chain
    (pkg_need_version_bump_show -> pkg_upstream_and_debian_changelog_bump
    -> pkg_verify_signed_commit -> pkg_git_sign_tags -> pkg_git_push_remotes
    -> pkg_git_push_tags) handles both kinds of repo:

    - pkg_need_version_bump_show: for specials, "needs version bump"
      means "HEAD has a signed commit but no signed tag at HEAD". No
      changelog sentinel check.
    - pkg_upstream_and_debian_changelog_bump: no-op for specials (no
      debian/changelog to bump).
    - pkg_git_sign_tags: for specials, use dm-quickgittagsign (tag name
      encodes HEAD SHA, unique per commit) instead of
      `genmkfile git-tag-sign` (which would try to recreate the existing
      nearest tag name and fail).
    - pkg_need_version_bump_and_pkg_build_and_reprepro_add: top-level
      dispatch - specials get the tag-and-push half, skip Debian
      build/reprepro entirely.

