        sink, matching the alert-17 autofix shape exactly).

    Where the target step already has a condition the guard is `&&`-
    ed onto it (reusable-scorecard.yml combines `always()` with the
    fork-PR guard; reusable-codeql.yml combines `inputs.dm-consumer-section != \'\'`).

    Honest note (already established in agents/security.md Threat
    model A and discussed on PR #92): the runtime mitigation
    (job-level guard + persist-credentials: false + no
    pull_request_target) was already in place. Step-level guards are
    cosmetic - they don\'t actually change what runs on a fork PR
    since the job-level guard already blocks the job. They are
    applied here for consistency with the alert-#17 autofix
    precedent, and to satisfy CodeQL\'s static analysis.

    Caveat: CodeQL\'s rule doesn\'t look at runtime guards (job-level
    or step-level if:); it looks at static properties. The alert-#17
    autofix flipped #17 open->fixed but the next scan opened #82 at
    the same line. Same shape may recur here. If that happens, the
    right answer is to add an actions/untrusted-checkout section to
    docs/scorecard-known-false-positives.md, not a workflow_run
    redesign (the trust model doesn\'t require one).

    reusable-pre-push-static.yml is untouched - it already has the
    guards from alert #17\'s autofix.

