    ci: convert apt-install-with-cache to a composite action

    Replaces the helper-script-at-fixed-path approach (ci/apt-install-with-cache.sh
    called from reusable workflows via .github/dmf/ci/...) with a
    GitHub composite action (.github/actions/apt-install-with-cache/),
    matching the existing .github/actions/install-deps and
    .github/actions/shellcheck pattern.

    Benefits:
      - One \'uses:\' line per consumer step instead of separate
        actions/cache + script-call steps.
      - Centralized cache-action SHA pin (one place to update on
        Dependabot bumps; reduces duplicate Dependabot PRs across
        consumers per agents/github-actions.md "Action SHA pinning").
      - Caller does not need to manually checkout developer-meta-files
        just to reach the install script; GitHub Actions checks the
        composite action out automatically when \'uses:\' is resolved.
      - Reusable for the local-* workflows in other consumer repos
        (msgcollector, security-misc) that today carry the same
        \'chown /var/cache/apt/archives + actions/cache\' bug.

    Structure (mirrors .github/actions/install-deps/):
      .github/actions/apt-install-with-cache/action.yml   (composite)
      .github/actions/apt-install-with-cache/install.sh   (seed/install/snapshot)

    Caller signature:
      - uses: org-ai-assisted/developer-meta-files/.github/actions/apt-install-with-cache@master
        with:
          packages: \'cppcheck yq\'
          cache-key: ${{ runner.os }}-apt-cppcheck-${{ hashFiles(\'.github/workflows/reusable-cppcheck.yml\') }}

    Removed:
      - ci/apt-install-with-cache.sh (moved to .github/actions/apt-install-with-cache/install.sh)
      - The bandit-workflow dmf-checkout reorder from the previous
        revision (no longer needed: the composite action self-checks-out).

