Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 15 18:59:23 2026 +0000

    ci(security): close remaining expression-injection sinks in run: blocks

    Follow-up to 3add64d2 ("Potential fix for code scanning alert no. 36:
    Code injection"), which fixed reusable-codeql.yml. Sweep of the
    remaining workflows turned up 10 more inline ${{ ... }} expressions
    interpolated into shell args inside run: blocks - the same pattern
    CodeQL's js/actions/command-injection (a.k.a. actions/expression-
    injection) query flags regardless of whether the underlying value is
    server-validated.

    Fix shape mirrors the autofix: route every value through step-level
    env: and consume with shell-native ${VAR} expansion in run:.

    Files touched:
    - reusable-bandit.yml         (1 sink: job.status)
    - reusable-cppcheck.yml       (1 sink: job.status; CPPCHECK_PATHS
                                   already routed via env)
    - reusable-scorecard.yml      (3 sinks: job.status, github.server_url,
                                   github.repository)
    - reusable-secrets-audit.yml  (5 sinks: 4x conditional 'present'/
                                   'absent' labels + job.status)

    For reusable-secrets-audit.yml the conditional 'present'/'absent'
    resolution is hoisted into the env: block - the expression engine
    evaluates it server-side before the env var is assigned, so the
    shell only sees a literal string.

    Verified clean by scanning all .github/workflows/*.yml and
    consumer-templates/.github/workflows/*.yml for the same pattern; 0
    hits remaining. YAML still parses, agents/pre-push-static.sh passes.

