commit 2fa3abe9b4b6748010b64e26d8bc0ab51642dff6
Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Thu May 14 18:38:12 2026 -0400

    consumer-claude-code: pre-filter @claude on comment events

    Surfaced during a GHA security audit against the patterns in
    https://securitylab.github.com/resources/github-actions-new-patterns-and-mitigations/.

    issue_comment and pull_request_review_comment triggers fire a runner
    spin-up on every comment. The reusable workflow's job-level if: then
    gates the actual work behind a @claude substring check + allowed-users
    roster. Doing the cheap substring test in the consumer wrapper too
    prevents the unnecessary runner spin-up for unrelated comments.

    This is an operational fix (saves CI minutes on noisy comment
    threads), not a security fix; the in-reusable gate already prevents
    unauthorized execution.

    Edits the canonical template under consumer-templates/. The active
    workflow under .github/workflows/ is updated in a follow-on commit
    to keep the byte-identical-across-consumers invariant intact.

