commit 18b99d47909c53c7c79b339a6a577db2bc886b09
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 23:01:55 2026 +0000

    bash-style-guide: add R-074 - no ; next-command chaining

    Generalises R-071 (case-arm: one statement per line) into a
    codebase-wide rule. Each bash statement gets its own line;
    bash's syntactic ; (case-arm ;; and C-style for-loop ;-separated
    clauses) are the only exceptions.

    Why on the line, not just in R-071: 'one statement per line in a
    case arm' is the narrow form; the user clarified the rule
    applies everywhere, not only inside case arms. Adjacent to R-070
    and R-071 since all three are about statement layout.

commit 1a253d866141c59a7d69bb42d44b1136c0b68445
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 22:58:58 2026 +0000

    bash-style-guide: R-160 example uses case-arm not ;-chained rm

    The previous R-160 'multiple rules at once' example showed two
    rm commands separated by ';' on the same line, then a trailing
    ';;'. That tripped both R-120 and R-070 naturally - which was the
    point of the example - but it ALSO implied that semicolon command
    chaining is a generally-accepted pattern in this style guide.
    It isn't. Replacing with the case-arm form, which has the same
    two-rule violation profile (rm + trailing ';;') without
    normalising '; next-command' as a routine pattern.

commit 0f98c0a08eb7e6e474e8bad533e0d4fd670ddf00
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 21:18:09 2026 +0000

    restore exec bit + fix R-102 regex regression

    The previous push_files commit (e6cc407) inadvertently:

    1. Reset agents/pre-push-static.sh and ci/coverity-download.sh
       from mode 100755 to 100644, causing the CI runner to abort
       with exit 126 ('Permission denied: ./agents/pre-push-static.sh').
       The MCP create_or_update_file / push_files tools both go
       through GitHub's contents API, which doesn't expose file
       mode and defaults new files to 100644. The original mode
       was lost on the rewrite.

    2. Doubled the backslashes in the R-102 regex on line 388 of
       agents/pre-push-static.sh: '\\b(bash|sh)...\\b' instead
       of the intended single-backslash '\\b...' word-boundary
       pattern. Inside a single-quoted bash string, JSON \\\\
       over-escaped to \\\\ instead of \\. As a regex, \\b
       matches a literal backslash followed by 'b' rather than the
       word boundary, so R-102 (no 'bash X.sh' / 'sh X.sh' interpreter
       prepend) was silently broken.

    Restoring via local commit because (a) the contents API has no
    file-mode parameter and (b) the local signing helper is returning
    HTTP 400 from the signing server in this environment - the
    commit is therefore unsigned (--no-gpg-sign) as a one-off; user
    authorized this in the conversation thread to unblock CI.

