commit 225c53d591a550e2ca4a17dd77ff15b3bbfe5077
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 20:28:06 2026 +0000

    github-actions.md G-A-006: drop event-type-differentiated pattern

    The 'Differentiated by event type' pattern used a constant
    event-class string ('pr' or 'tag') as the only discriminator in
    the concurrency group, collapsing all PRs into one '<workflow>-pr'
    group. Under cancel-in-progress: true, that caused a new push on
    PR-2 to cancel the in-flight build on PR-1 - cross-PR cancellation
    has no defensible semantics.

    The stated motivation (preventing a PR push from cancelling a
    multi-hour tag build) is already satisfied by the standard
    per-ref pattern, because github.ref is unique per PR
    (refs/pull/N/merge) and per tag (refs/tags/<tag>). Tag and PR
    refs differ, so cancel-in-progress: true cannot cross those
    boundaries.

    Delete the section and add a one-paragraph note under the
    Cancellable pattern explaining that per-ref grouping already
    covers the single-workflow-file-handles-PR-and-tag case.

    The only live use of the broken pattern - derivative-maker
    local-test-build.yml - is being fixed in a sibling PR.

