commit e94efb5ed1ed14e6ff4871f7ad3d7dc130479f0e
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 19:51:54 2026 +0000

    chmod +x dm-github-* + policy libs to satisfy check-shebang gate

    Pre-commit-hooks' check-shebang-scripts-are-executable hook flags
    every changed text file that has a '#!' shebang but lacks the
    executable bit. The two dm-github-* scripts and the two policy libs
    have '#!/bin/bash' but were mode 100644 in the index, so the hook
    fired on this PR's diff.

      * usr/bin/dm-github-org-policy
      * usr/bin/dm-github-personal-policy
        Originally landed as 100755; mode dropped to 100644 in commit
        9a02558 ('Collapse duplicated rationale comments to G-NNN
        cites'). That commit pre-dates the consumer-pre-push-static.yml
        workflow + check-shebang hook (both landed 2026-05-11 via
        4f2b89e), so it never tripped CI. Restoring 100755 - these are
        invoked directly as commands and must be executable.

      * usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/github-policy-data.bsh
      * usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/github-policy-lib.bsh
        Sourced libs; the shebang is an editor / shellcheck hint, not
        an invocation contract. Making them 100755 is harmless (the
        files just declare readonlys / functions and exit if executed
        directly) and is the minimal-impact fix to satisfy the hook
        without removing the editor hint.

commit 72f6bfa32073616aa90cf804d018f296f875a3de
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 19:46:20 2026 +0000

    policy libs: add R-010 strict-mode quintet to satisfy gate

    The pre-push static gate's R-010 check flags every changed shell
    file whose head -100 lacks the 6-line strict-mode block. Both
    github-policy-data.bsh (pure data) and github-policy-lib.bsh
    (sourced helper) had zero strict-mode lines because they are
    sourced rather than executed. Editing them in this PR surfaced
    the latent gate failure.

    Same fix shape as 34b1afb (which completed the strict-mode block
    in dm-packaging-helper-script after the same gate fire): add the
    six lines to the lib header. No behavior change for the existing
    callers (dm-github-org-policy, dm-github-personal-policy, and the
    ci/tests/test_*.sh harness all set the same options on themselves
    before sourcing); for any future non-strict caller the lib now
    self-enforces strict mode.

commit e3114c943e154874f2b509066e66e62608fa18c3
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 19:41:22 2026 +0000

    dm-github-* policy: drop required_signatures rule on MIRROR / BOT

    The bot account (BOT_USERS, e.g. assisted-by-ai) and the bot org
    (MIRROR_ORGS = org-ai-assisted) push commits via AI-assisted
    automation that does not own a GPG key matching the bot's
    GitHub-verified identity. The ruleset 'required_signatures' rule
    ("allow only signed commits") therefore blocked every legitimate
    bot push on those roles.

    Split the per-role rules array the same way bypass actors are
    already dispatched:

      POLICY_RULESET_RULES_SOURCE / _PERSON  -> includes
                                                required_signatures
      POLICY_RULESET_RULES_MIRROR / _BOT     -> omits it

    Wired through policy_branch_ruleset_body / policy_tag_ruleset_body
    (new 4th arg, defaults to the with-required_signatures variant for
    back-compat). dm-github-org-policy and dm-github-personal-policy
    resolve POLICY_RULESET_RULES_${kind^^} alongside the existing
    POLICY_RULESET_BYPASS_${kind^^} dispatch.

    SOURCE (Kicksecure / Whonix) and PERSON (maintainer's personal
    mirror) still enforce signed commits/tags. New unit test
    test_ruleset_body_rules_dispatch.sh pins the rule-types contract
    per role.

