commit 643d44c55ca347f6da71685d008c63805f296bca
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 19:25:02 2026 +0000

    workflow triggers: normalize pull_request to branches: [master]

    Three universal consumer templates had bare `pull_request:`
    without a base-branch filter, while the matching push trigger
    and the other templates (bandit, codeql-actions/cpp/python,
    cppcheck) use `branches: [master]`. Drift from the standard
    pattern. Tighten:

    - consumer-claude-code.yml
    - consumer-codex-review.yml
    - consumer-pre-push-static.yml

    Each gains `pull_request: branches: [master]`. Other triggers
    (issue_comment + pull_request_review_comment on claude-code,
    workflow_dispatch.inputs.pr_ref on codex-review) preserved.

    Practical impact: PRs targeting feature branches stop firing
    the AI reviews + style gate. PRs targeting master (the typical
    org pattern) are unaffected. Anyone wanting AI review on a
    non-master PR can workflow_dispatch manually.

    Canonical + hub-runtime updated in lockstep; consumer repos
    get the propagated update via pkg_update_consumer_workflows
    (or via the per-repo PRs that immediately follow this one).

