commit 0cb638fc1abf34808c9392111e28e4a1b918cdb8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 18:25:23 2026 +0000

    pre-push-static: fix fail() one-arg invocation in run_precommit_hook

    `fail()` references both $1 (rule tag) and $2 (message). Under
    `set -o nounset` the line

        "${hook}" "${@}" || fail "${hook}"

    triggers an unbound-variable error when any pre-commit-hook
    fails, because $2 is unset. Surfaced via the double-quote-
    string-fixer auto-fixing ci/tests/test_workflow_yaml.py during
    the consumer-template rollout (see dmf #69 thread for the
    diagnosis log).

    Fix: pass a placeholder message; the hook itself has already
    printed its diagnostic to stderr by the time we get here.

    Other 8 fail() callers in this script already pass 2 args; this
    was the lone offender.

