commit 6800ea3e70da3af65f53b0e13f2592aa5c2f0398
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 16:06:02 2026 +0000

    reusable-bandit: shebang-aware Python discovery; universal wrapper

    Per spec "Parameter ownership" classifications for bandit:

    - paths: removed. Shebang-aware discovery in the reusable
      finds Python by `.py` extension OR `^#!.*python` first-line
      match. Catches genmkfile's '*.py#tag' files and Debian-
      libexec scripts without extension - the org's common case.
    - severity-level / confidence-level: hardcoded at medium /
      medium (the previous defaults).
    - skips: removed. Per-repo suppressions use bandit's
      `# nosec` inline comments. (Open implementation question
      per the spec: if a real use case for per-repo skip lists
      appears, promote `bandit.skips` to dm-consumer.yml.)
    - prepare-command: removed. The shebang scan eliminates the
      need for genmkfile-tagged-source symlink hacks
      (ci/codeql-prepare.sh, ci/python-prepare.sh).
    - timeout-minutes: hardcoded at 10.

    New files:

    - ci/bandit-discover-python.sh: NUL-separated Python file
      discovery (extension + shebang). Excludes .git/,
      .github/dmf/, and submodule paths from .gitmodules.
    - consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-bandit.yml:
      byte-identical wrapper, no `with:`.
    - .github/workflows/consumer-bandit.yml: hub-runtime copy
      (dmf has Python in ci/ and usr/bin/).

    Reusable changes:

    - workflow_call.inputs block removed entirely - bandit is now
      a universal template (no per-repo state).
    - Runs on ubuntu-24.04 for consistency with other refactored
      reusables.
    - Bandit invocation: discovery script | xargs -0
      --no-run-if-empty -- bandit -ll -ii --.

    workflow_list in dm-packaging-helper-script:
    bandit.yml -> consumer-bandit.yml.

    Hard switch. Consumers (msgcollector, security-misc) still
    pass `with: paths:` and `with: prepare-command:`; those are
    silently ignored after this lands. Their next bandit run will
    scan the whole repo via shebang discovery rather than the
    previous scoped paths. False positives (if any) need migration
    to `# nosec` or per-repo migration PRs to add the wrappers
    themselves.

commit 9e4309309c02213ae7302b2e18b16170ea6488a0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 15:58:02 2026 +0000

    reusable-codeql: dm-consumer.yml runtime read + add codeql-cpp

    Single-reusable design (one reusable-codeql.yml serves all
    language wrappers), parameterized by language input and new
    optional `dm-consumer-section` input that names the section
    to read per-repo prepare-command / build-command from.

    Spec section naming (per user-confirmed decision 1a):

    - codeql-actions: empty dm-consumer-section -> no runtime read.
      Universal byte-identical wrapper. No per-repo state.
    - codeql-python: dm-consumer-section='codeql-python'. Optional
      prepare-command. Soft-skip if file or section absent.
    - codeql-cpp:    dm-consumer-section='codeql-cpp'. Optional
      prepare-command. Required build-command when build-mode=manual;
      reusable hard-fails on missing key.

    Inputs changed:

    - `prepare-command` removed (replaced by dm-consumer.yml read).
    - `build-command` removed (replaced by dm-consumer.yml read,
      required when build-mode=manual).
    - `timeout-minutes` removed (hardcoded at 30; both python and
      c-cpp scans on the existing consumers fit in 30 min).
    - `dm-consumer-section` added (optional, default empty; the
      source-of-truth for which section to read).
    - `language`, `build-mode`, `queries` unchanged.

    Hard switch (no backward compat). Consumers passing the old
    `with: prepare-command:` or `with: build-command:` will have
    those inputs silently ignored. For c-cpp consumers with
    build-mode=manual but no codeql-cpp.build-command in
    dm-consumer.yml, the reusable hard-fails at workflow start.
    Immediate consumer migration PRs needed for kloak (codeql-cpp),
    security-misc (codeql-cpp + codeql-python prepare-command), and
    helper-scripts (codeql-python; no prepare-command needed).

    New files:

    - consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-codeql-cpp.yml
      (canonical, byte-identical wrapper; NOT installed in this hub
      since dmf has no C/C++).

    Changed files:

    - consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-codeql-python.yml
      and the hub-runtime copy: pass `dm-consumer-section:
      codeql-python` so security-misc's per-repo prepare-command can
      flow through. Soft-skip for repos without the section (e.g. dmf
      itself, msgcollector, helper-scripts).
    - dm-packaging-helper-script: workflow_list adds
      consumer-codeql-cpp.yml.

    Spec: agents/github-actions-consumer-templates.md.

