commit 97de3949bcd11f21654f931b9b4cb77b4611f01c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 15:17:25 2026 +0000

    reusable-coverity: drop concurrency block (deadlock hotfix)

    Empirically observed via failed workflow_dispatch on kloak's
    post-#67 consumer-coverity.yml: GitHub Actions deadlock detector
    fires when both the consumer wrapper and the reusable declare
    the same concurrency group ("Canceling since a deadlock was
    detected for concurrency group: 'Coverity' between a top level
    workflow and 'coverity'").

    `github.workflow` inside a reusable resolves to the CALLER's
    workflow name, so the wrapper's `group: ${{ github.workflow }}`
    ("Coverity") collides with the reusable's identical group.
    Documented in agents/github-actions.md G-A-006 "Reusable-side
    concurrency"; reusable-bandit / reusable-cppcheck /
    reusable-pre-push-static / reusable-scorecard /
    reusable-secrets-audit all omit concurrency for the same reason.

    Why did this not surface before #67? The pre-#67 reusable had
    a job-level `if:` (canonical-repos input check). Possibly that
    evaluation gated lock acquisition; this turn's refactor removed
    the job-level if (replaced with step-level gate), which may have
    changed when the concurrency lock is taken. Either way, the
    fix is the same: remove the duplicate group; the wrapper's
    singleton suffices.

    Caller contract preserved: the byte-identical wrapper still has
    `group: ${{ github.workflow }}` + `cancel-in-progress: false`,
    so the org-wide singleton property holds.

commit 9d01bb6bd962caf88e782519ff28b527a917ed51
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 15:08:34 2026 +0000

    reusable-cppcheck: hard switch to dm-consumer.yml runtime read

    Parallel to the coverity refactor in #67. Mirror changes:

    Inputs removed:

    - paths -> dm-consumer.yml `cppcheck.paths` (required).
    - prepare-command -> dm-consumer.yml `cppcheck.prepare-command`
      (optional, empty -> no source-tree prep step).
    - enable -> hardcoded at "warning,performance,portability".
    - extra-args -> removed entirely (promote to dm-consumer.yml on
      first real need).
