    - Load per-repo config from .github/dm-consumer.yml (id: cfg).
    - Source-tree prep (gated on cfg.prepare_command != '').
    - cppcheck invocation uses ${CPPCHECK_PATHS} from cfg, hardcoded
      enable list.

    Plus a new consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-cppcheck.yml
    canonical wrapper - no `with:` block, byte-identical across
    consumers.

    Hard switch: consumers still passing `with: paths:` etc. will
    have those inputs silently ignored after this merges - the
    reusable schema no longer declares them. helper-scripts /
    security-misc cppcheck wrappers will need consumer migration
    PRs (dm-consumer.yml + rename) immediately after this lands.

