commit dbdb16f83e4fbd83a33d1ec654d96ccdb46f2bba
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 14:57:24 2026 +0000

    batch 7 + coverity hard refactor

    Two things in one PR per the user's "bigger batch sizes" guidance:

    1. batch 7: claude-code consumer-wrapper rename, completing the
       universal-template prefix sweep for developer-meta-files.

    2. Coverity hard refactor: reusable-coverity.yml drops every
       workflow_call.input except secrets and switches to runtime
       read of .github/dm-consumer.yml in the consumer repo. Adds
       the new consumer-coverity.yml canonical wrapper in
       consumer-templates/ (not installed in this hub - no C/C++ to
       scan).

    ## reusable-coverity changes

    Inputs removed (now read from .github/dm-consumer.yml at runtime):

    - apt-packages, build-command, project-name, canonical-repos
    - timeout-minutes (hardcoded at 30)
    - dry-run (hardcoded at false; no wrapper override per spec)

    New step structure:

    - Install yq (kislyuk python-yq, pinned to ubuntu-24.04)
    - Load per-repo config from .github/dm-consumer.yml (id: cfg)
      - Required keys: project-name, canonical-repos (hard-fail on
        missing/empty)
      - Optional keys: apt-packages, build-command (empty -> default
        behavior)
      - Hyphenated yml keys translate to underscored $GITHUB_OUTPUT
        names (GitHub Actions expression parses outputs.foo-bar as
        subtraction)
      - Newline-rejection on every value (format injection protection)
    - Canonical-repos gate (id: gate) - emits allowed=true/false
      based on cfg.canonical_repos vs github.repository. Strict by
      design: workflow_dispatch no longer bypasses (the previous
      reusable allowed that; fork-side manual dispatches burn
      runner time for nothing since secrets aren't available to forks).
    - All expensive steps (Sanity check, Prepare apt cache, Cache,
      Install build deps, Download Coverity, Build, Submit) gated by
      if: steps.gate.outputs.allowed == 'true'.

    Secret-env placement: COVERITY_TOKEN / COVERITY_EMAIL /
    COVERITY_PROJECT move out of jobs.<id>.env: and onto the
    individual gated steps that need them (Sanity check / Download /
    Submit). Pre-gate steps and non-canonical runs never see secret
    values - the gate placement is meaningful, not cosmetic.

    Hard switch, not backward-compatible: consumers passing 'with:'
    inputs (apt-packages, build-command, project-name, canonical-repos)
    will see those inputs silently ignored after this merges - the
    reusable schema no longer declares them. Each consumer
    (helper-scripts, kloak, security-misc) needs an immediate
    follow-up PR: add .github/dm-consumer.yml with the required keys
    and rename coverity.yml -> consumer-coverity.yml byte-identical
    to the canonical template.

    ## claude-code rename

    Standard universal-template prefix sweep. No behavior change.

