commit a050fb16d65149c80feb063a92d02764d3698fb0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 14:35:36 2026 +0000

    batch 4: add consumer-codeql-python.yml; clear stuck GHAS check-run

    New universal-ish template: 'python' CodeQL scan, analogous to
    the existing 'actions' CodeQL scan. Installed in this hub
    (developer-meta-files contains Python in usr/bin/dm-* tools,
    ci/ scripts, libexec/ helpers).

    Functional motivation - this clears a flaky GitHub Advanced
    Security behavior the previous batches hit on PRs #62, #63:

    - GHAS auto-detects this repo as having Python and speculatively
      creates a 'CodeQL' check-run on each commit. Without a workflow
      that submits Python SARIF, GHAS keeps that check-run queued.
      Sometimes it eventually times out / resolves (PR #61), sometimes
      it stays queued forever (PR #62, #63). The queued stub flips
      the PR's mergeable_state to 'unstable' and blocks auto-merge.
    - Adding this workflow submits a real Python SARIF on every push
      and PR, which gives GHAS the analysis it expects and clears
      the stub.

    Architectural motivation - feature parity with codeql-actions:

    - consumer-codeql-actions.yml scans the 'actions' language
      (workflow YAML security).
    - consumer-codeql-python.yml scans the 'python' language
      (security-and-quality suite, default reusable settings).

    Files:

    - New: consumer-templates/.github/workflows/consumer-codeql-python.yml
      (canonical, per spec).
    - New: .github/workflows/consumer-codeql-python.yml
      (hub-runtime copy, byte-identical).
    - dm-packaging-helper-script: workflow_list adds
      consumer-codeql-python.yml. Repos without Python should not
      install this; the file-presence opt-in rule applies.

    Spec: agents/github-actions-consumer-templates.md.

