        kloak:                '0 5 * * 0'
        security-misc:        '30 5 * * 0'
        developer-meta-files: '0 6 * * 0'
      is dropped. Byte-identical propagation forbids per-repo cron
      rewrites at propagation time.
    - All consumers will run on '0 6 * * 0' (developer-meta-files's
      prior slot, chosen to minimize change for this hub). GitHub's
      cron queue serializes the simultaneous fires; Scorecard's low
      value-to-noise ratio makes the queue contention acceptable.
    - Other repos shift to '0 6 * * 0' the next time
      pkg_update_consumer_workflows lands the new wrapper there.
      Until then they keep their old per-repo slot - no immediate
      multi-repo coordination change.

