commit 0b5e8e7e4846ed39158c4bdc5984293026bc1c86
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 13:39:33 2026 +0000

    agents: fourth-round spec fixes per review

    Four precision fixes addressing the fourth-round review on PR #60:

    - Config-load loader rewritten to translate hyphenated yml keys
      to underscored $GITHUB_OUTPUT names. GitHub Actions expression
      syntax parses `outputs.foo-bar` as subtraction, not as a
      hyphenated property; the hyphen-to-underscore translation
      happens in the loader via `${key//-/_}`. Downstream steps now
      use plain `steps.cfg.outputs.project_name` dot syntax rather
      than the bracket form.
    - Coverity workflow_dispatch behavior change documented. Today's
      reusable's job-level `if:` treats workflow_dispatch as an
      unconditional bypass of canonical-repos; the step-level gate
      is intentionally stricter. Rationale: a fork-side manual
      dispatch would burn runner time for nothing (the org's
      COVERITY_SCAN_TOKEN is not available to forks), and the
      upstream's quota is now never at risk from cross-fork manual
      triggers.
    - yq install comment dropped the "ubuntu-latest is currently
      Ubuntu 24.04" assumption. Recommendation added that
      parameterized reusables pin `runs-on: ubuntu-24.04` (not
      `ubuntu-latest`) so the contract is not silently broken if a
      future Ubuntu LTS swaps in mikefarah/yq via apt.
    - Direct-callers clarifier tightened to note that
      dm-consumer.yml-owned values are removed from
      workflow_call.inputs entirely, so direct-call from a
      hand-written local-*.yml can only pass the surviving
      workflow_call.inputs - not the values that moved to
      dm-consumer.yml.

commit 443062c02c5fb685d3bd6aac43a7c6ab281e1834
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
