commit c0c9a52910f4653d428e1f79d90e8bd8bdec9636
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 12:16:38 2026 +0000

    agents: add consumer-template architecture spec; expand G-A-005 prefix scheme

    G-A-005 grows from a two-way (reusable- vs unprefixed) to a
    three-way (reusable- / consumer- / local-) filename convention.
    consumer-X.yml is the new prefix for thin wrappers around
    reusables; local-X.yml is the new prefix for hub-private or
    repo-private workflows that never propagate.

    The new agents/github-actions-consumer-templates.md is the
    companion architecture spec:

    - consumer-templates/.github/workflows/ as the single source of
      truth for every consumer-*.yml in the org;
    - pkg_update_consumer_workflows propagation is pure 'cp' - no yml
      parsing, no yml writing, no manifest, no opt-in/opt-out flags;
    - opt-in is filesystem-driven (presence of consumer-X.yml in the
      consumer's .github/workflows/ is the opt-in signal);
    - per-repo parameters for parameterized templates live in the
      consumer's .github/dm-consumer.yml and are read by the relevant
      reusable at workflow runtime, not at propagation time;
    - the runtime read pattern with hard-fail validation and
      newline-rejection protection against \$GITHUB_OUTPUT format
      injection.

    developer-meta-files is documented as a consumer of itself - the
    same propagation tool maintains the hub's own consumer-*.yml
    copies. No special-case logic for the hub.

