commit 5f113b0b531bc5dd59e09844f6cf5870fb9c58f2
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 08:09:37 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: add pkg_install_codeql_actions_scan

    Companion to pkg_update_consumer_workflows but with INSTALL-if-
    missing semantics for rolling out a NEW shared consumer wrapper to
    the org. pkg_update_consumer_workflows uses pkg_update_if_exists,
    which by design skips destinations that don't already carry the
    file - correct for ongoing UPDATE bumps but wrong for the initial
    rollout of codeql-actions.yml, where every target repo legitimately
    lacks the file.

    Behavior:
    - Source: dmf's canonical .github/workflows/codeql-actions.yml
      (the one PR #57 just landed).
    - Skips packages with no .github/workflows/ directory (repos that
      don't use GitHub Actions at all).
    - Skips packages that already carry codeql-actions.yml (idempotent;
      re-runs no-op).
    - Otherwise: cp the file in, git add, git commit "add ...".
    - Runs through nothing_to_commit guard before commit.

    Scope it inherits via run_batch: every kicksecure/whonix submodule
    under packages/*, plus the qubes-template-* and Whonix-Installer /
    Whonix-Starter / derivative-maker special-cases at the bottom of
    run_batch (line 2544 for derivative-maker). dmf itself self-skips
    via the "already carries the file" branch.

    Kept as a separate function rather than folding INSTALL semantics
    into pkg_update_consumer_workflows because the two contracts differ:
    - UPDATE-if-exists: idempotent re-sync of canonical content; safe
      to schedule, never adds files unexpectedly.
    - INSTALL-if-missing: one-shot rollout of a brand-new wrapper;
      intentionally adds files.

    Mixing them in one function would risk a future caller accidentally
    spreading every wrapper in the list to every repo with a
    .github/workflows/ directory.

