commit 1bff421f146a9c1ba8ea04c5b098f737e7c50b34
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Tue May 12 07:21:28 2026 +0000

    github-actions: harden caches against poisoning; doc G-A-007

    Drop the catch-all 'restore-keys:' fallbacks in reusable-bandit,
    reusable-cppcheck, and reusable-coverity. The primary key already
    binds to hashFiles(<this workflow>); the fallback prefix matched
    any historical entry for the OS and is the foothold pattern called
    out in
    https://adnanthekhan.com/2024/05/06/the-monsters-in-your-build-cache-github-actions-cache-poisoning/

