commit dee023339946798f85aaa2050f629783cead5009
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 22:47:33 2026 +0000

    self-consumers: switch from './' to '@master' for canonical-source consistency

    Drops the dev-meta-files self-consumer asymmetry. Each of the five
    self-consumer wrappers now references the reusable the same way a
    cross-repo consumer does:

      uses: org-ai-assisted/developer-meta-files/.github/workflows/reusable-X.yml@master

    instead of the previous './.github/workflows/reusable-X.yml'.

    Side effect this enables: dev-meta-files's own .github/workflows
    becomes a drop-in canonical_workflows_dir for the new
    pkg_update_consumer_workflows helper - the cross-repo wrappers
    propagated to submodules are now byte-identical to the wrappers
    that live here, no rewrite step.

    Tradeoff: a PR that modifies a reusable's workflow YAML no longer
    exercises its own changes during the PR's CI run (with '@master',
    the PR's scorecard.yml etc. invoke master's reusable, not the
    PR's). The dual-checkout pattern in reusable-pre-push-static.yml
    and reusable-secrets-audit.yml still dogfoods the bash scripts
    those reusables invoke - only the workflow YAML itself loses
    PR-CI coverage. Acceptable given the canonical-source benefit;
    post-merge scheduled / dispatched runs continue to verify
    end-to-end behavior.

    Updated wrappers:
    - claude-code.yml
    - codex-review.yml
    - pre-push-static.yml
    - scorecard.yml
    - secrets-audit.yml

    Docstrings trimmed to drop the now-obsolete 'self-consumer
    dogfoods via local path' framing; each one points at the reusable
    on GitHub the same way the cross-repo wrappers do.

commit 9e2cefefdd022f008791a5d06412208d39ad242c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 22:38:40 2026 +0000

    dm-packaging-helper-script: add pkg_update_consumer_workflows

    Bulk caller of pkg_update_if_exists for the cross-repo consumer
    wrapper set (bandit, claude-code, codeql, codex-review, coverity,
    cppcheck, pre-push-static, scorecard, secrets-audit). Iterates the
    fixed list; for each, sources from <canonical_workflows_dir>/<name>
    (passed as the batch-command argument), targets
    ${batch_current_package_path}/.github/workflows/<name>. Source
    absence is logged and skipped (a package may not carry every
    consumer wrapper); destination absence is silently skipped by
    pkg_update_if_exists's "if exists" semantic, so brand-new repos
    without a given wrapper are no-op'd.

    Caller-supplied canonical_workflows_dir lets the user point at a
    templates dir of cross-repo wrappers; dev-meta-files's own
    .github/workflows is NOT suitable (self-consumer wrappers use a
    local "./" uses: path).

