commit d2d59b2728a85c930538d47de8128443ab687479
Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 16:25:15 2026 -0400

    workflows: workflow_dispatch + PR-keyed concurrency + reusable trigger-asymmetry doc (#54)

    ## Changes

    Three related changes in `.github/workflows/`:

    1. **`workflow_dispatch:` added** to `claude-code.yml` and
    `pre-push-static.yml` (the two consumer wrappers that lacked it).
    2. **Concurrency group key fixed** in `claude-code.yml` and
    `codex-review.yml`. Plain `${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.ref }}` is
    wrong for `issue_comment` / `pull_request_review_comment` events because
    `github.ref` resolves to the default branch on those events -- so
    unrelated PRs' comment-triggered runs would queue into the same group.
    New key:
       ```
    ${{ github.workflow }}-${{ github.event.pull_request.number ||
    github.event.issue.number || github.ref }}
       ```
       matches what the reusable already uses.
    3. **Brief trigger-asymmetry comment** added to
    `reusable-claude-code-review.yml` and `reusable-codex-review.yml`
    explaining why each carries different consumer-side triggers (Claude is
    mention-driven; Codex is PR-open-driven with `workflow_dispatch` for
    fork-PR re-runs). Locks in the asymmetry as intentional.

    ## Why

    - **`workflow_dispatch:` consistency:** lets admins manually re-run any
    workflow without an empty commit. Org convention going forward: every
    consumer wrapper has it.
    - **Concurrency fix is the CI-time lever:** pushing 5 commits to a PR
    currently fires 5 full claude-code runs that all complete (no
    cancellation because the comment-event group key is wrong). With the
    PR-number-keyed group, the first 4 get canceled on each new push; only
    the tip commit's run completes. Effectively the "only the tip triggers
    CI" pattern.
    - **Trigger asymmetry doc:** future normalization passes won't try to
    merge Claude and Codex triggers, since they have different feature sets
    (mention vs no-mention) by design.

    This PR is the model for analogous changes in the other 7 repos with
    AI-review consumers that have NO concurrency block at all. Those follow
    in separate per-repo PRs once this lands.

    ## Mandatory Checklist

    - [x] Legal agreements accepted. [Terms of
    Service](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Terms_of_Service), [Privacy
    Policy](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Privacy_Policy), [Cookie
    Policy](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Cookie_Policy), [E-Sign
    Consent](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/E-Sign_Consent),
    [DMCA](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/DMCA),
    [Imprint](https://www.kicksecure.com/wiki/Imprint)

    ## Optional Checklist

    - [x] I have tested it locally (pre-push gate passes; trigger blocks
    parse).
    - [x] I have reviewed and updated any documentation if relevant (the
    trigger-asymmetry comment in the reusables IS the documentation).

    Fixes #

    https://claude.ai/code/session_018rti4CCm2SQ3PWKa7jRt7p

