commit 6688771884f8f03ff5ef74c69ef031101a084c8e
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 15:40:47 2026 +0000

    step-summary-emit: canonical printf '%s\n' form for emission

    Two changes:

    1. Default-value line: drop the printf -v trick and use plain
       parameter expansion + assignment instead, matching the
       project's existing pattern in github-org-lib.bsh /
       github-org-clone:

           GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY="${GITHUB_STEP_SUMMARY:-/dev/null}"

       Three iterations of this line (':' -> 'true' -> 'printf -v')
       were all symptoms of trying to host a parameter-expansion
       assignment on a command. The cleaner form has no command at
       all.

    2. emit() body: rewrite from multi-character printf format
       strings to building a parts=() array of literal lines + a
       single printf '%s\n' "${parts[@]}" emission. Matches R-030's
       canonical 'printf %s\\n "..."' form throughout, with the format
       string a literal '%s\n' and all data passed as args.

