commit ce5e4c9069197c61addf0935ac2060feacfffea8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 14:27:22 2026 +0000

    reusable-coverity: add dry-run input

    Lets a caller test changes to the workflow / build command without
    consuming Coverity Scan's 1-build-per-day submission slot. The
    cov-int.tgz artifact still uploads (always:if step), so the
    operator can inspect what would have been submitted.

    Implementation: coverity-submit.sh always runs the tar pack;
    DRY_RUN=true short-circuits before the curl submission, prints a
    summary of project / version / description / archive size, and
    exits 0. Workflow plumbs `DRY_RUN: \${{ inputs.dry-run }}` as the
    step's env var so the script's existing CI-guard remains in
    charge of the run mode.

    Naming matches the input on vapier/coverity-scan-action so a
