commit a974f5ba676705ccc490064899c3d7e051da50f8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 13:53:41 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: emit SOURCE-only UI-flip notices for Dependabot + code-scanning

    Five settings have a known desired state on SOURCE orgs but no
    documented REST setter as of 2026-05. The OpenAPI spec at
    github/rest-api-description has zero Dependabot fields in the
    PATCH /repos/{owner}/{repo} security_and_analysis block (only
    secret-scanning fields), no auto-triage-rules paths, no grouped-
    security-updates path, and no per-repo dependency-graph PUT.
    Some endpoints exist on api.github.com (e.g. .../dependabot/
    alerts/auto-triage-rules returns 403 with a bare token) but are
    intentionally outside the public OpenAPI surface, so scripting
    against them risks silent breakage.

    Add a `policy_skip_ui_repo` helper to github-policy-lib.bsh
    mirroring the existing `policy_skip_ui` but substituting
    __OWNER__ and __REPO__ for per-repo URLs, then wire five new
    SOURCE-only skip notices into dm-github-org-policy:

      org-level:
        - Dependabot grouped security updates: enable in UI
        - Code scanning: recommend security-extended query suite

      per-repo:
        - Auto-triage rule "Dismiss low-impact dev-scoped" must be OFF
        - Auto-triage rule "Dismiss package malware alerts" must be OFF
        - Prevent direct Dependabot alert dismissals (delegated): enable

    All five are gated on `kind == 'source'` because Dependabot is off
    entirely on MIRROR / PERSON / BOT (per the existing canonical-vs-
    mirror split), and MIRROR repos use the reusable codeql.yml
    workflow (advanced setup, ignores the org default-setup query-
    suite recommendation).

    Document the new operator-action surface in
    agents/github-policy-canonical-vs-mirror.md under a new
    "SOURCE-side UI-only operator flips" section, including a brief
    note on Dependabot version updates being file-driven via
    dependabot.yml (no toggle, no skip line, audit_org_state already
    reports presence). Extend test_dm_dryrun_source_vs_mirror.sh
    to assert the five new skip lines appear on SOURCE and never on
    MIRROR.

commit 7d3635aa0eeea55642b2f7fd1c3eee94bb3e1da7
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 13:34:07 2026 +0000

    agents+ci: add --per-commit mode to pre-push-static; restore cross-link note

    agents/pre-push-static.sh: extracted the file-content checks
    into run_file_checks() and added a --per-commit flag. In
    per-commit mode the script iterates each commit in base..HEAD
    via detached checkout (saved-and-restored via EXIT trap), with
    base_ref reset to the per-commit parent for each pass. Catches
    violations that existed mid-branch but were fixed before the
    tip -- the default union-diff mode misses these because it
    diffs the merge-base against HEAD.

    Usage:
       agents/pre-push-static.sh                    # union, vs @{u}
       agents/pre-push-static.sh origin/master      # union, vs master
       agents/pre-push-static.sh --per-commit origin/master   # per-commit

    The commit-message R-001 check stays in union mode regardless;
    per-commit iteration would re-check the same messages N times
    for no extra coverage.

    AGENTS.md: restored the 'Other repos cross-link here rather
    than duplicating' note that was lost in the compaction pass.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_018rti4CCm2SQ3PWKa7jRt7p

commit 4f2b89e9211737333e2df23ac736bb19974c13c3
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 13:18:34 2026 +0000

    agents+ci: fold pre-commit-hooks (direct execution) into pre-push-static.sh; unify gates

    Folds ci/precommit-hooks-gate.sh into agents/pre-push-static.sh
    so there is now ONE gate, ONE script, ONE CI workflow.

    agents/pre-push-static.sh:
      + is_text_file() helper: extension match first, 'file --mime'
        fallback for extension-less text files (shell scripts named
        'foo' with a shebang, ...).
      + check_precommit_hooks(): probes for the 'check-yaml' binary
        as a representative of the upstream pre-commit-hooks set;
        skips silently with one note if absent. Otherwise builds
        per-type file lists (text, text+exec, symlink, yaml, json,
        toml, xml, python, requirements) and invokes the curated
        hook set on the matching subsets:
          filename-blind: check-added-large-files,
                          check-case-conflict, destroyed-symlinks,
                          forbid-new-submodules
          text:           check-merge-conflict, check-vcs-permalinks,
                          detect-aws-credentials, detect-private-key,
                          fix-byte-order-marker, end-of-file-fixer,
                          trailing-whitespace-fixer,
                          mixed-line-ending,
                          check-shebang-scripts-are-executable
          text+exec:      check-executables-have-shebangs
          symlink:        check-symlinks
          by extension:   check-yaml, check-json, check-toml,
                          check-xml, check-ast,
                          check-builtin-literals,
                          debug-statement-hook,
                          double-quote-string-fixer,
                          pretty-format-json,
                          requirements-txt-fixer

    Graceful-skip on missing binaries means the local hook still
    catches the bash-style-guide rules even on dev machines that
    haven't installed pre-commit-hooks (Ubuntu noble apt lacks the
    package; only Debian trixie has it). CI runs in trixie so
    catches both.

    .github/workflows/reusable-pre-push-static.yml: switched from
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest to container: debian:trixie-slim and
    expanded the inline apt install to cover ca-certificates, file,
    git, pre-commit-hooks, shellcheck. Single container, single
    gate.

    Deleted (superseded):
      .github/workflows/reusable-precommit-hooks.yml
      .github/workflows/precommit-hooks.yml
      ci/precommit-hooks-gate.sh

    misc/pre-commit-config.yaml: kept as documentation of the
    intended hook list. The script is the source of truth now.

