commit 98817116ed19a50b17bc5ee17f17693404d5144c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 13:00:25 2026 +0000

    ci: rewrite precommit-hooks gate as bare-binary calls (no pre-commit framework, no pip)

    The earlier attempt called pre-commit-hooks binaries directly
    without per-hook file-type filtering, then pivoted to the
    upstream pre-commit framework to get correct filtering for free.
    Org preference is to avoid the framework entirely (auditable
    tooling) and avoid pip (apt-only on Debian-derivative installs).

    This commit: bare-binary calls with per-hook filtering done
    locally in ci/precommit-hooks-gate.sh, modeled on each hook's
    upstream 'types:' declaration:

      filename-blind  check-added-large-files, check-case-conflict,
                      destroyed-symlinks, forbid-new-submodules
      text            check-merge-conflict, check-vcs-permalinks,
                      detect-aws-credentials, detect-private-key,
                      fix-byte-order-marker, end-of-file-fixer,
                      trailing-whitespace-fixer, mixed-line-ending,
                      check-shebang-scripts-are-executable
      text+exec       check-executables-have-shebangs (the hook that
                      failed CI when given the unfiltered list)
      symlink         check-symlinks
      by extension    check-{yaml,json,toml,xml,ast,builtin-literals},
                      debug-statement-hook, double-quote-string-fixer,
                      pretty-format-json, requirements-txt-fixer

    Workflow: container: debian:trixie-slim. apt-only install;
    pre-commit-hooks isn't in Debian bookworm or Ubuntu noble apt,
    but trixie has 5.0.0+dfsg-5. ci/install-pre-commit-hooks.sh
    deleted -- the install collapses to 4 lines inline in the
    workflow (R-100 allows since no control flow).

    misc/pre-commit-config.yaml: minimum_pre_commit_version restored
    to '4.2.0' since the framework is no longer in use; the constraint
    is documentation-only at this point.

    is_text_file() in the gate script: extension match first (cheap),
    'file --mime' fallback for files without a known extension. Same
    heuristic the upstream 'identify' library uses, just narrower.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_018rti4CCm2SQ3PWKa7jRt7p

