commit 9b88fd2f0dba3924e9d414f5f70f930df1f9ad80
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 12:39:50 2026 +0000

    ci: add reusable-precommit-hooks gate; abolish usr/bin/dm-precommit-bare

    Moves the never-finished local-hook draft (usr/bin/dm-precommit-bare,
    which exited rc=1 after printing 'TODO') into a working CI gate.
    Same hook list, run on the same model as reusable-pre-push-static
    (install on the runner, run against changed files vs the base ref,
    dogfood via a dmf consumer wrapper).

    New files:
      ci/install-pre-commit-hooks.sh
        Tries 'apt-get install pre-commit-hooks' first (Debian trixie,
        Ubuntu plucky/questing/resolute carry the package). Falls back
        to 'pip install --break-system-packages pre-commit-hooks' on
        Ubuntu noble (24.04 = ubuntu-latest), where the apt package is
        NOT in the archive even though 'pre-commit' the framework is.
        Both paths land the same upstream binary set on PATH.

      ci/precommit-hooks-gate.sh
        Runs the curated subset of upstream pre-commit-hooks against
        changed files in HEAD vs the base ref ($1, default
        origin/master). Filename-blind hooks (check-added-large-files,
        check-merge-conflict, detect-private-key, end-of-file-fixer,
        trailing-whitespace-fixer, ...) get every changed file.
        Type-specific hooks (check-yaml, check-json, check-toml,
        check-xml, check-ast, ...) get filtered file lists.

      .github/workflows/reusable-precommit-hooks.yml
        Reusable workflow: two checkouts (caller + dmf), install hooks,
        run the gate. Same shape as reusable-pre-push-static.yml. No
        concurrency block per the secrets-audit precedent.

      .github/workflows/precommit-hooks.yml
        Dogfooding consumer wrapper. Triggers on pull_request and
        push-to-master.

