Author: assisted-by-ai (Bot Account) <228987186+assisted-by-ai@users.noreply.github.com>
Date:   Mon May 11 04:45:48 2026 -0400

    test_workflow_yaml: add W-007 (dependabot.yml required when direct third-party SHAs present)

    Conditional rule: if the repo has direct third-party action
    SHA pins in its workflows / composites, it must have
    .github/dependabot.yml (otherwise SHA bumps go untracked).

    Repos with zero direct refs are exempt - they only use
    '@master' references to dmf reusables, and dmf's single
    Dependabot config propagates SHA bumps to them via
    reusable workflow chains. Empirically: genmkfile and kloak
    (0 direct refs each) correctly don't have their own
    dependabot.yml.

    Empirical: tightening surfaces 6 repos that need
    dependabot.yml (tb-updater, msgcollector, Whonix-Installer,
    usability-misc, security-misc, whonix-firewall); companion
    PRs add the baseline to each.

