    Compact-output topics array in metadata-sync audit drift line

    The audit-drift display formerly printed the topics JSON array
    pretty-printed across multiple lines, which made each drifting
    repo span 4+ log entries. Pass --compact-output to the three jq
    invocations that produce the JSON arrays compared by audit:
    metadata_topics_json (the cached desired form) and the two
    in-audit sort filters (desired-sorted and current-sorted). Each
    audit drift line now fits on a single log entry.

    No behaviour change otherwise: equality comparison still holds
    when both sides use the same compact form, and the apply path
    sends the array via --argjson which parses identically either
    way.

