    Add dm-github-org-metadata-sync

    Apply per-repo description, homepage, and topics from
    repo-metadata.bsh to each selected GitHub owner. Default targets
    the mirror org (org-ai-assisted); ORGS_OVERRIDE switches to the
    source-side bucket ('Kicksecure,Whonix,adrelanos') for runs with
    the other PAT.

    - Move repo-metadata.bsh into usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/ so
      it is shipped by the existing 'usr/*' debian install glob and
      sourced from the tool at runtime.
    - Add POLICY_REPO_METADATA and POLICY_REPO_TOPICS tuples to
      github-policy-data.bsh; bodies are jq templates with per-call
      --arg / --argjson substitution.
    - New script reuses policy_tool_init (mode flags, deps,
      warn-flag), policy_api_call (dry-run + warn tracking),
      ghorg_list_repos (one GET per owner for existence set),
      ghorg_validate_name (G-001).
    - Topic format validated per repo-metadata.bsh contract
      (^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9-]*$, len<=50, count<=20).
    - ci/tests/test_dm_metadata_dryrun.sh exercises --dry-run against
      the org-ai-assisted fixture.
