commit 39cabbf47e3b8746703aef4288e913e2eb4ed8df
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 16:12:03 2026 +0000

    PVR off everywhere (canonical disclosure is the wiki)

    Earlier this PR enabled PVR on SOURCE while disabling it on
    MIRROR. That is the wrong policy for our org: the canonical
    vulnerability-disclosure channel is the wiki page linked from
    org-ai-assisted/.github/SECURITY.md (kicksecure.com/wiki/
    Reporting_Bugs#Security_Vulnerabilities + the Vulnerability
    Disclosure Policy page). Enabling PVR alongside that would
    split the disclosure inbox between the wiki flow and a parallel
    GitHub-side flow.

    Move PVR off everywhere:

      - dm-github-org-policy apply_repo_policy: REPO_PVR_OFF call
        moved out of the kind-pivot if/else and into an
        unconditional step. Runs on both SOURCE and MIRROR every
        --apply.
      - github-policy-data.bsh: POLICY_REPO_PVR (the PUT-style
        enable variant) deleted; replaced with a rationale comment
        pointing at .github/SECURITY.md. POLICY_REPO_PVR_OFF stays;
        label de-suffixed from "disable PVR (mirror)" to plain
        "disable PVR" since it now runs everywhere.

    Dependabot pair stays SOURCE-on / MIRROR-off. Dependabot is
    about CI scanning of dependencies, not about disclosure inbox
    routing - the duplicate-alerts argument that excludes Dependabot
    from MIRROR does not apply to PVR's "where do reports land"
    question, and vice versa.

    agents/github-policy-canonical-vs-mirror.md: tables and bullet
    points reworked to separate the two concerns. The Free-plan
    replacements table now shows PVR as "off everywhere", explicit
    in both columns. The Summary table splits the old "Dependabot +
    PVR" row into two.

    Tests:
      test_dm_apply / test_dm_dryrun: assert "disable PVR" without
        the (mirror) suffix.
      test_dm_dryrun_source_vs_mirror: SOURCE side now expects
        "disable PVR" (was "enable PVR"); MIRROR side unchanged.
        Forbidden block on both sides catches "enable PVR" leaking
        in (since the PUT constant no longer exists, this asserts
        the data-file removal too).

    Live verified against org-ai-assisted: exit 0, 0 warns. All 108
    MIRROR repos see "disable PVR" idempotent (HTTP 204).

