commit b077592952cc35fe03f01f97da948f3015ae0db8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 16:00:06 2026 +0000

    agents: web_commit_signoff_required is DCO, not GPG

    Earlier wording in the future-tightenings list framed
    web_commit_signoff_required as "closes a small bypass against
    the GPG-required-signatures ruleset". That conflated two
    unrelated mechanisms:

      - required_signatures ruleset rule: cryptographic signature
        on commits (GPG / SSH / web-flow GPG). Already on in our
        rulesets. Web-UI commits already satisfy this because
        GitHub's web-flow GPG key signs them.
      - web_commit_signoff_required: textual DCO Signed-off-by
        trailer on web-UI commits. License/copyright attestation,
        no cryptography involved.

    There is no GPG bypass to close. Replace the entry with the
    correct framing: web_commit_signoff_required is a DCO
    attribution mechanism (https://developercertificate.org/),
    worth enabling only if Kicksecure / Whonix formally adopts
    DCO. Otherwise it just adds UI friction with no benefit.

