commit de3e1404bd8f56396b5bbf1e1bb886a3d4f77934
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 10:58:35 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: actively disable Dependabot + PVR on MIRROR

    Previous SOURCE-only commit gated the enable side but left the
    mirror in a stuck state if the older un-gated apply had ever run
    (or if a UI flip ever turned them on). Switch the mirror branch
    of apply_repo_policy from a single skip line to an active disable
    trio so every --apply reconciles. No new mode flag.

    Three new POLICY_REPO_*_OFF entries (DELETE on the same paths):
      POLICY_REPO_DEPENDABOT_ALERTS_OFF
      POLICY_REPO_DEPENDABOT_FIXES_OFF (carries EXTRA_OK_STATUS=422)
      POLICY_REPO_PVR_OFF

    Order at the call site: FIXES_OFF BEFORE ALERTS_OFF. The DELETE
    /automated-security-fixes endpoint returns HTTP 422 once
    Dependabot alerts are off ("alerts are off" - security updates
    cannot exist without alerts). Doing FIXES first on the cold path
    avoids the 422 entirely; on subsequent idempotent runs it returns
    422 which the new EXTRA_OK_STATUS knob captures as success.

    Library change: policy_apply_org / policy_apply_repo dispatchers
    now look up an optional POLICY_<NAME>_EXTRA_OK_STATUS constant
    and forward it as the 5th arg to policy_api_call. Used here for
    FIXES_OFF; precedent existed for direct calls in
    dm-github-personal-policy (POLICY_PAGES_DELETE) but the
    dispatcher did not expose the knob until now.

    Tests:
      test_dm_apply / test_dm_dryrun / test_dm_dryrun_source_vs_mirror
      updated to assert the disable trio on MIRROR side, with
      forbidden-block guards to catch SOURCE-only enable lines
      leaking onto MIRROR (and vice versa).

    Fixtures: 9 new DELETE_repos_org-ai-assisted_*_{vulnerability-
    alerts,automated-security-fixes,private-vulnerability-reporting}
    files for derivative-maker, helper-scripts, some-fork. The
    automated-security-fixes fixture returns HTTP 422 to exercise the
    EXTRA_OK_STATUS=422 path on every run.

    Verified live against org-ai-assisted (108 repos, Free plan):
      first run:   869 ok / 5 skip / 0 warn / exit 0
                    (each MIRROR repo: 3x 204 disables)
      second run:  869 ok / 5 skip / 0 warn / exit 0
                    (each MIRROR repo: FIXES_OFF [422], ALERTS_OFF
                    [204] idempotent, PVR_OFF [204] idempotent)
      state on org-ai-assisted/developer-meta-files:
        vulnerability-alerts:           HTTP 404 (off)
        automated-security-fixes:       enabled=false
        private-vulnerability-reporting: enabled=false
        secret_scanning + push_prot:    still enabled (kept)

