commit 54e65290299443369669802455d067687f7c90b7
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 08:41:17 2026 +0000

    metadata/repo-metadata.bsh: introduce per-project metadata file

    Source of truth for description, website, and topics applied across
    every clone of each project (Kicksecure / Whonix / org-ai-assisted /
    adrelanos). Format is one add_repo call per project, named-arg style.
    Apply tool dm-github-org-metadata-sync is a separate follow-up; this
    commit lands the data file only so entries can be reviewed and
    expanded in isolation.

    Org layout encoded:
      Most projects live in EXACTLY ONE canonical org (Kicksecure OR
      Whonix - never both). REPO_HOME field names which one ('k' or 'w').
      org-ai-assisted and adrelanos are mirror-of-everything; the apply
      tool will fan each entry to the canonical org plus both mirrors,
      skipping silently when a repo does not exist in a particular owner.

    The apply tool will NEVER create or fork repositories. Missing repos
    in any owner are reported and skipped. Repo creation / forking stays
    a deliberate one-time human action via github-org-fork or the GitHub
    UI - not something a metadata-sync run should ever trigger.

    Initial entries (10): security-misc, hardened-kernel, tirdad,
    sdwdate, helper-scripts, derivative-maker, kloak, corridor,
    onion-grater, developer-meta-files. Wiki URLs probed live and all
    return HTTP 200; helper-scripts and developer-meta-files have no
    canonical wiki page so website is left empty rather than misleading.

commit 049a04a05cf66b0fefbd3063b2214bd902b551aa
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 01:52:39 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: gate Dependabot + PVR to SOURCE-only

    The Dependabot alerts / Dependabot security updates / PVR PUTs
    added in the previous commit are SOURCE-only on the org side.
    Running them on MIRROR (a fork org of SOURCE) would duplicate
    every alert the canonical SOURCE repo already raises - the same
    anti-duplication logic that keeps these off in
    dm-github-personal-policy on the personal mirror.

    apply_repo_policy in dm-github-org-policy now gates the three
    PUTs on kind=='source'. On MIRROR a single skip line stands in:
      skip: <owner>/<repo>: Dependabot alerts + security updates +
      PVR - mirror would duplicate upstream SOURCE notifications

    This affects only the active MIRROR run today (the active orgs
    list is MIRROR_ORGS only). When SOURCE_ORGS is enabled, those
    orgs get the full per-repo Dependabot/PVR fan-out as before.

    Branch + tag rulesets and secret scanning + push protection are
    applied on both kinds (the bypass-actor list is the only ruleset
    diff). Same on the personal-policy side: PERSON and BOT both
    keep secret scanning + rulesets, both skip Dependabot.

    Tests:
      test_dm_apply, test_dm_dryrun: assert the skip line, plus a
      forbidden block to catch SOURCE-only lines leaking to MIRROR.
      test_dm_dryrun_source_vs_mirror: pin the per-side fan-out -
      Dependabot/PVR DRY-RUN lines on SOURCE (Whonix), the skip line
      on MIRROR (org-ai-assisted), neither side sees the other's
      fragments.

    Fixtures:
