Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 00:29:12 2026 +0000

    github-policy-data: PERSON repo body adds has_issues=false

    Match BOT and MIRROR. The personal account is a backup mirror;
    issues, like wikis / project boards / discussions, belong on the
    upstream org repo where reports route to maintainers and tooling
    expects to find them. Splitting an inbox between the upstream
    issue tracker and the personal mirror is the same anti-pattern
    that motivated has_issues=false on the org-side MIRROR body.

    PERSON and BOT bodies are now identical on the touched fields.
    The split is preserved so a future PERSON-only divergence does
    not need the dispatcher reworked.

