      test_dm_personal_dryrun_person_vs_bot - new PERSON label
      'wiki/issues/projects/discussions off, secret-scan on'.

commit 92ddd742f3e5451028fff66a91bfc7449c9452ae
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun May 10 00:18:20 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: per-repo Free-plan equivalents for paid features

    The previous commit commented out the org-level code-security
    configuration POST and the org-level branch+tag rulesets because
    both fail on a Free org (HTTP 400 GHAS / HTTP 403 Team+).

    This commit restores the dropped coverage by fanning out the same
    intent across per-repo endpoints that work on Free for public
    repos. Empirically tested 2026-05 against org-ai-assisted (Free,
    108 repos): --apply now exits 0 with 869 ok lines and zero warns
    (was 114 ok + 3 skip + 3 warn / exit 1 two commits ago, then
    113 ok + 5 skip + 0 warn / exit 0 in the previous commit).

    Per repo, apply_repo_policy now also calls:

      PATCH /repos/{o}/{r}                       (was already there)
        body now includes security_and_analysis.{secret_scanning,
        secret_scanning_push_protection}.status = enabled

      PUT /repos/{o}/{r}/vulnerability-alerts         (NEW)
      PUT /repos/{o}/{r}/automated-security-fixes     (NEW)
      PUT /repos/{o}/{r}/private-vulnerability-reporting   (NEW)

      POST/PUT /repos/{o}/{r}/rulesets   x2           (NEW)
        branch ruleset (deletion, non_fast_forward, required_signatures)
        tag    ruleset (same three rules)
        bypass actor list pivots on org_kind via
        POLICY_RULESET_BYPASS_{SOURCE,MIRROR} (un-commented from
        previous commit; plan-independent at repo scope).

    Data file:
      POLICY_REPO_SOURCE / POLICY_REPO_MIRROR bodies now include
      security_and_analysis.
      Three new POLICY_REPO_DEPENDABOT_ALERTS / _DEPENDABOT_FIXES /
      _PVR entries with empty {} bodies (the PUTs accept a body and
      this avoids a no-body special case in policy_apply_repo).

    Tests:
      test_dm_apply / test_dm_dryrun / test_dm_dryrun_source_vs_mirror
      updated to assert on the new ok / DRY-RUN lines and the new
      MIRROR/SOURCE label format.

    Fixtures:
      Added 5 per repo for the 3 fixture repos (15 total): three PUTs
      for the security toggles plus GET + POST for the per-repo
      rulesets list-then-create dance.

    dm-github-personal-policy is left alone in this PR. Its existing
    exceptions (Dependabot deliberately off; "duplicate notifications
    for findings already raised on the upstream org-side repo") are
    intentional design - the personal account is a backup mirror and
    disclosure should flow upstream. Same logic applies to PVR there.
    The comment in dm-github-personal-policy already documents the
    "if this becomes the canonical home, uncomment" toggle.

