commit 056000ba320958fa8ab81242045b7060bfbab6a9
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 20:40:21 2026 +0000

    github-policy-data: drop members_can_create_internal_repositories from POLICY_MEMBERS

    Same bug class as PR #11 (allow_forking): the body included a
    field that GitHub validates against the org plan tier before
    applying anything. On Free/Team/Pro orgs the field is locked
    server-side at false, and GitHub rejects the entire PATCH with
    HTTP 422 'Validation Failed: This organization does not support
    internal repositories.' Unlike allow_forking, this rejection
    does NOT silently apply the other body fields - the validation
    is hard, so default_repository_permission, members_can_create_
    repositories, members_can_create_{public,private}_repositories
    all roll back along with the bad field.

    Verified against org-ai-assisted (free plan): pre-fix --apply
    left members_can_create_repositories=true,
    members_can_create_public_repositories=true,
    members_can_create_private_repositories=true (drift) because
    every PATCH on POLICY_MEMBERS rolled back due to the internal-
    repos field.

    Drop the field from the body. Effect by plan tier:
      Free/Team/Pro: feature unavailable, server-side locked at
                     false, omission is a no-op.
      Enterprise:    feature available; explicit setter belongs in
                     a separate plan-tier-specific policy block
                     (the script's ORGS array does not yet
                     distinguish plan tier).

