commit f0d7cae6b046f903fc194aff64885566a59964fe
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 19:40:38 2026 +0000

    github-policy-data: drop allow_forking from POLICY_REPO_MIRROR

    Same bug class as the recent POLICY_PERSONAL_REPO_BOT fix. The
    per-repo PATCH against MIRROR-org repos was sending allow_forking:
    false in its body; GitHub rejects it with HTTP 422 ('This
    organization does not allow private repository forking') because
    the org-level forking_allowed_for_private_repositories setting is
    the actual gate, and the per-repo PATCH cannot diverge from it.
    The 422 invalidates the entire request - GitHub then silently
    applies the other body fields anyway, leaving allow_forking
    unchanged and the apply step reporting failure across all 108
    mirror repos in org-ai-assisted.

    Discovered via dm-github-org-policy --apply rc=1 with 108 x 422
    WARNs, all carrying the same 'private repository forking' message.
    Spot-checked org-ai-assisted/derivative-maker and helper-scripts:
    has_wiki/has_issues/has_projects/has_discussions all flipped to
    false (silent partial apply); allow_forking stayed true.

    Drop allow_forking from POLICY_REPO_MIRROR body + label, update
    the SOURCE-vs-MIRROR diff comment to reflect that allow_forking
    is org-level only, and prune the now-vacuous 'allow_forking=off'
    entries from the test forbidden-string lists.

