commit 7e7650e6203c92d0da384987fdb9f47038c380e1
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 19:13:04 2026 +0000

    Remove ci/tests/test_die_if_not_has.sh

    The test pinned a defensive 'die_if_not_has github-org-fork'
    startup check in dm-github-org-policy via PATH manipulation.
    Two reasons to drop both the test and (eventually) its target:

    1. The defensive check guards a state the package manager does
       not allow: dm-github-org-policy and github-org-fork ship in
       the same .deb. After 'apt install developer-meta-files' you
       cannot have one without the other.

    2. The test was fragile-by-design - 'genmkfile install' in CI
       puts github-org-fork on /usr/bin, so PATH-based hiding has
       to evict /usr/bin entirely (env -i + minimal PATH), which
       does not match how the script ever runs in practice.

    The behavioral half - 'die_if_not_has actually exits non-zero
    and names the missing command' - is helper-scripts behavior and
    belongs upstream in that repo's test suite, not here.

