commit 7eb3a7a65735a6e19349ca45d4fa6c1c4ce04b93
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 18:58:31 2026 +0000

    test_die_if_not_has: only pass HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH if set

    Previous attempt defaulted to /usr when unset, which then resolves
    the source paths in the script to /usr/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/..
    - the script dies with a 'source: No such file' error before ever
    reaching die_if_not_has, so the fragment assertions fail.

    CI installs helper-scripts to system paths so HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH
    stays unset there. The script's '${HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH:-}/usr/...'
    expansion correctly resolves to /usr/libexec/helper-scripts/...
    when the var is empty, which is the install location.

    Local dev workflows can still export HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH and it
    will be honored.

