commit 503885a876890136dd372b819fff6d468d1e304c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 18:55:19 2026 +0000

    test_die_if_not_has: env -i PATH=minpath only

    Pre-existing failure on master since the workflow added 'genmkfile
    install' before the test runs: that step installs github-org-fork
    into /usr/bin, so the old PATH=minpath:/usr/bin:/bin spec exposed
    the system-installed binary and die_if_not_has never fired.

    Switch to 'env -i PATH=minpath' (no /usr/bin, no /bin). On Debian
    trixie's merged-/usr layout /bin is a symlink to /usr/bin, so
    dropping /usr/bin alone would not have been enough. env -i also
    strips the inherited environment for hermeticity; HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH
    is re-injected because the script sources lib files from there.

