commit c2e05cd9f682671798f88a0453ba39a06e05ade5
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 10:40:58 2026 +0000

    ci/tests: random-input fuzz for validator + ghorg_jq_capped

    Two property-style fuzz tests covering the highest-value attack
    surfaces in the github-org-* / dm-github-* tooling that didn't
    fit Hypothesis (which lives in helper-scripts on the Python
    helpers; the bash dispatch surface here doesn't justify a Python
    harness).

      test_fuzz_validate_name.sh         500 random inputs from 5
                                         distributions (urandom bytes,
                                         ASCII printable, charset-
                                         restricted, edge cases,
                                         single-char). Each input is
                                         run through ghorg_validate_name
                                         AND a pure-bash oracle that
                                         mirrors the documented rule
                                         set; any divergence fails.
                                         Catches accidentally-permissive
                                         regex changes, off-by-one
                                         length-cap breakage, missing
                                         reserved-name checks.
                                         ~20s. Iterations boost-able
                                         via TEST_FUZZ_VALIDATE_NAME_ITERS.

      test_fuzz_ghorg_jq_capped.sh       Stress test of the byte-cap +
                                         timeout wrapper against
                                         pathological stdin inputs:
                                           100 KB /dev/urandom + tiny cap
                                           deeply-nested array (parser
                                                       stack-depth probe)
                                           10 MB string token (tokenadd-
                                                       class CVE probe)
                                           UTF-8 surrogate halves (jv
                                                       unicode probe)
                                           valid-JSON positive control
                                         Asserts: termination within
                                         timeout+slack, no segfault, no
                                         hang, cap fires when expected.
                                         <1s. Stress, not coverage-
                                         guided fuzzing - that lives
                                         upstream at jqlang/jq.

    Implementation note in-source: under R-010 pipefail, 'tr ... |
    head -c N' SIGPIPEs the producer when head closes early
    (rc=141 propagates to the calling shell). Both tests use the
    'read fixed blob then bash-slice' pattern (${var:0:N}) instead
    to avoid the SIGPIPE class.

    Local timings: validate_name 18-21s, jq_capped <1s. The
    validator fuzz is the slow one because each reject calls
    sanitize-string (Python) via the log helper - 500 iters at
    ~40 ms each. Lowered the default iteration count from a
    draft 2000 to 500 so the test fits comfortably in the rest of
    the suite without a thorough-mode boost knob.

