commit e4055de61240947a26a565bec1410bf4c4f0a5a2
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 9 10:11:41 2026 +0000

    github-org-lib: ghorg_jq + ghorg_jq_capped wrappers (parser-CVE depth)

    Two wrappers for jq, used at every jq call site in the
    github-org-* / dm-github-* tool family:

      ghorg_jq          wall-clock timeout via 'timeout
                        --kill-after=${HARD} ${SOFT}'. For hardcoded
                        bodies (POLICY_* constants etc.).
      ghorg_jq_capped   same timeout + 'head -c ${GHORG_JQ_MAX_BYTES}'
                        stdin cap (default 4 MiB). For paths where the
                        bytes piped to jq came from an external API.

    Defaults are GHORG_JQ_TIMEOUT_SOFT=10s, _HARD=2s, _MAX_BYTES=4 MiB
    ($((4*1024*1024))) - all overridable from the caller's environment.

    Why both: --kill-after is mandatory because if a parser bug leaves
    jq's signal handler blocked or in an uninterruptible state, the
    SIGTERM at the soft deadline is silently ignored. --kill-after
    schedules a follow-up SIGKILL the kernel delivers regardless of
    process state.

    Footgun caught: 'timeout' does NOT support '--' as end-of-options
    between DURATION and COMMAND - it interprets the literal '--' as
    the command name (yields 'timeout: failed to run command --').
    R-062 already excludes timeout from the verified list; commit
    documents this in-source so a future maintainer doesn't re-add.

    Converted every jq call site:
      github-org-lib.bsh             pipes from API responses ->
                                     ghorg_jq_capped
      github-policy-lib.bsh          ruleset-list parse -> _capped;
                                     hardcoded body factories ->
                                     ghorg_jq
      dm-github-org-policy           hardcoded jq programs ->
                                     ghorg_jq; API-body parse paths
                                     (audit_org_state, code-security
                                     list, ruleset list) ->
                                     ghorg_jq_capped
      dm-github-personal-policy      audit body parses -> _capped
      dm-github-token-test           rate-limit body parses -> _capped

    Documented in agents/security.md under new 'Parser-level trust
    assumptions' section: explicit list of trusted parsers, what we
    deliberately don't sandbox, the wrappers' purpose, and the
    gojq / bubblewrap escalation path if a future CVE makes the
    trade-off shift.

    Behavior verified by --dry-run on dm-github-org-policy: 118
    DRY-RUN log lines on org-ai-assisted, unchanged from pre-
    refactor. All jq operations succeed within the 10s timeout.

