        a local; apply_org_policy was inconsistent with itself.

    Resolve kind once at the top with explicit '|| return 1', then
    use the constant naming convention to look up the right bypass
    list via bash indirect expansion (POLICY_RULESET_BYPASS_${kind^^}).
    The case statement is gone; one less branch in the apply sequence.

    Same convention then collapses apply_repo_policy's two-line
    'name=...; policy_apply_repo ... "${name}"' into a single
    inline 'REPO_${kind^^}' arg.

    Behavior verified via dry-run.

commit 3e51810c45446b68ac4fe7376220df048299b124
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 20:14:02 2026 +0000

    policy: lift labels, endpoints, methods, UI URLs to data file

    The previous round moved policy bodies to github-policy-data.bsh
    but left labels, endpoint paths, HTTP methods, and UI URLs as
    string literals in the apply_* functions. They were policy data
    hiding inside dispatch code.

    Each simple PUT/PATCH/POST/DELETE policy is now a 4-tuple of
    constants in the data file:
      POLICY_X            body  (jq program)
      POLICY_X_ENDPOINT_*   API path with __ORG__ / __OWNER__ / __REPO__
                            / __ID__ placeholders
      POLICY_X_METHOD       HTTP verb
      POLICY_X_LABEL        operator-facing description for log lines

    UI-only policies (2FA, PAT toggles, Apps) carry POLICY_X_UI_URL
    constants instead of endpoints; URLs use __ORG__ placeholders.

    New dispatcher helpers in github-policy-lib.bsh resolve a NAME to
    the right 4-tuple via indirect bash expansion ('${!var}'):

      policy_apply_org   <org> <NAME> [<endpoint_suffix>]
      policy_apply_repo  <owner> <repo> <NAME> [<endpoint_suffix>]
      policy_skip_ui     <org> <NAME> [<url_suffix>]

    apply_org_policy is now a flat dispatch table:
       policy_apply_org "${org}" FORK_PR_APPROVAL
       policy_apply_org "${org}" WORKFLOW_PERMS
       policy_apply_org "${org}" ACTIONS_SCOPE
       policy_apply_org "${org}" ACTIONS_ALLOWLIST ENDPOINT
       policy_apply_org "${org}" MEMBERS
       policy_skip_ui   "${org}" 2FA
       apply_code_security_config "${org}"
       ## ruleset upserts (different machinery)
       policy_skip_ui   "${org}" PAT
       ## App URL skip (uses two URLs)

    apply_repo_policy in dm-github-org-policy reduces to:
       kind="$(org_kind "${owner}")"
       policy_apply_repo "${owner}" "${repo}" "REPO_${kind^^}" ENDPOINT

    apply_repo_policy in dm-github-personal-policy is similarly flat
    (dispatcher for steps 1-4, custom call for the Pages DELETE step
    which needs the extra-ok-status arg the dispatcher does not
    handle).

    Renames:
      POLICY_REPO -> POLICY_PERSONAL_REPO  to disambiguate from
                                            org-side POLICY_REPO_SOURCE
                                            / POLICY_REPO_MIRROR.

    Verified: 'jq -n .* '\''{' grep across the three files returns
    zero matches; dry-runs against org-ai-assisted and adrelanos
    produce identical log lines pre/post-refactor.

