commit 71edb6a904b5296a633c2e0cc9046dd8f09f9bde
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 19:42:18 2026 +0000

    policy data: extract to github-policy-data.bsh (single source of truth)

    Final step of the policy-readability refactor. All POLICY_*
    constants - both shared and consumer-specific - now live in a new
    github-policy-data.bsh, sourced by both dm-github-org-policy and
    dm-github-personal-policy.

      github-policy-data.bsh        NEW: pure data, no functions, no
                                    API calls. Three sections:
                                      - Shared (FORK_PR_APPROVAL,
                                        WORKFLOW_PERMS,
                                        ACTIONS_ALLOWLIST)
                                      - Org-policy (CODE_SECURITY,
                                        ACTIONS_SCOPE, MEMBERS,
                                        REPO_SOURCE/MIRROR,
                                        RULESET_BYPASS_SOURCE/MIRROR
                                        + the SOURCE-vs-MIRROR diff
                                        table)
                                      - Personal-policy
                                        (ACTIONS_DISABLED, REPO)

      github-policy-lib.bsh         No data; only API helpers
                                    (policy_api_call, policy_upsert_*_
                                    ruleset, parameterized ruleset
                                    body factories) and the shared
                                    arg-parser.

      dm-github-org-policy          Sources the data file; the local
                                    'Policies' block at top is gone
                                    (data lives one file over now).
                                    SOURCE_ORGS / MIRROR_ORGS arrays
                                    stay (they are the WHO, not the
                                    WHAT).

      dm-github-personal-policy     Same - sources the data file,
                                    local POLICY_* block removed.

    Why a separate file: a maintainer who wants to know 'what GitHub
    settings does this tooling touch?' opens one file, sees every
    POLICY_* in one place. Adding a new policy is a one-file edit;
    which consumer references it is a separate decision in the apply_*
    function.

    Bonus: 'show_help' is invoked dynamically by policy_parse_mode_args
    through bash dynamic scoping; shellcheck cannot prove the call
    graph statically. Suppress SC2317 inline on the function with a
    note explaining why.

