commit 9010cffead440dd73e7cce8e49654ad6907718db
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 16:20:32 2026 +0000

    dm-github-org-policy: SOURCE/MIRROR org distinction + mirror-side issues=off

    Two kinds of org are touched by this script. Make the distinction
    obvious at the top of the file (where future readers look first)
    and pivot per-repo policy on org name:

      SOURCE = canonical upstream (Kicksecure, Whonix)
        has_issues=true    file bugs here
        has_wiki=false

      MIRROR = fork org (org-ai-assisted) for AI-assisted dev work
        has_issues=false       file everything upstream
        has_projects=false     project boards belong upstream
        has_discussions=false  Discussions belong upstream
        has_wiki=false

    Vocabulary (SOURCE_ORGS / MIRROR_ORGS) aligns with what
    dm-github-fork-sync already uses internally so a reader can move
    between the two scripts without re-mapping.

    The MIRROR-side trackers were previously left at GitHub's defaults
    (issues on, projects on, discussions on); contributors would
    either get split inboxes (issue filed on the mirror, never seen by
    upstream maintainers) or not file at all. Forcing them off makes
    'file upstream' the only path.

