commit ee8784b2a99e0cdc8d134db1a07b344ad7597e69
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 8 11:53:25 2026 +0000

    coverity reusable: clarify token vs email secret scope

    COVERITY_SCAN_TOKEN must be set as a repo-level secret per consumer
    because tokens are scoped per Coverity project on
    scan.coverity.com. Document this explicitly in the reusable's
    header so operators do not waste time trying to set it org-wide
    and getting opaque 'project=X token mismatch' errors from
    scan.coverity.com on submission.

