commit 4c5c67da874e993641c564246e2eeb7b2f8042ea
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu May 7 22:46:43 2026 +0000

    github-actions: codeql reusable - add prepare-command input

    Some repos (Kicksecure-style packages with #package-tag suffixes on
    filenames) need source-tree manipulation before the CodeQL extractor
    crawls files - in particular, the python/javascript extractors
    discover sources by file extension, so a 'foo.py#tag' source has to
    be symlinked to 'foo.py' before init.

    Adds an optional 'prepare-command' bash hook between checkout and
    init. Empty default means existing callers (helper-scripts, kloak)
    keep their current zero-step prelude.

commit c5085accbfb256cf22257321c5e396a6d2df1d39
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu May 7 22:37:53 2026 +0000

    github-actions: add reusable CodeQL workflow

    Centralizes the CodeQL boilerplate that was being duplicated across
    repos (helper-scripts python-only, kloak c-cpp+python). One job per
    (language, build-mode) tuple, parameterized via workflow_call inputs:
    language, build-mode, build-command, queries, timeout-minutes.

    Hardened defaults match what helper-scripts already had: workflow-
    level 'contents: read', fork-PR guard, explicit timeout (default
    30 min), 'security-and-quality' query pack, and an explicit
    'category:' on analyze for clean multi-language SARIF separation.

    Schedule is intentionally NOT defined here (workflow_call cannot
    own a 'schedule:'); the caller wrapper supplies its own cron slot.

