commit abd7353124fe9be431b1f4cbf468c2d09d1adce8
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu May 7 20:00:13 2026 +0000

    Add reusable Scorecard workflow

    First reusable workflow in developer-meta-files. Eliminates the
    ~70-line scorecard.yml duplication currently maintained in
    derivative-maker and helper-scripts. Other repos that adopt
    Scorecard can consume this one too.

    Caller invokes via:

      jobs:
        scorecard:
          uses: Kicksecure/developer-meta-files/.github/workflows/scorecard.yml@master
          permissions:
            security-events: write
            contents: read
            actions: read

    Schedule and branch_protection_rule triggers MUST stay at the
    caller level - GitHub Actions does not allow schedule under
    workflow_call. Each caller picks a cron slot that doesn't collide
    with the other repos in the org.

    Carries forward the pinned action SHAs (checkout v6.0.2, scorecard-
    action v2.4.3, upload-artifact v7.0.1, codeql-action upload-sarif
    v4.35.3 - the newer of the two SHAs the existing copies use), the
    fork-PR guard (no-op unless the caller routes pull_request events
    in), and the 'publish_results: false' default (off the OpenSSF
    public transparency log unless the project opts in).

