commit 9fbe616581295c85d351a8c96e56078036cf7eff
Author: claude-code <claude-code@assisted-by-ai>
Date:   Thu May 7 17:52:20 2026 +0000

    github-org-* / dm-github-*: restore LOG_MAX_LEN cap; refactor body capture; expand mock-API tests

    Background: commit 9e141a6 ("remove ghorg_safe_print from lib files;
    log() sanitizes internally") removed the per-call-site
    ghorg_safe_print wrapper that had been applying the
    GHORG_MAX_DISPLAY_LEN=256 byte cap manually. The justification was
    that helper-scripts log() pipes every message through
    sanitize-string internally - which is true for ANSI / control / HTML,
    but not for length: log() reads "${LOG_MAX_LEN:-nolimit}" and with
    LOG_MAX_LEN unset the cap is "nolimit" (no truncation). Net regression:
    a hostile or misbehaving GitHub API response, bounded only by curl
    --max-filesize=10MB, could flow through every log warn unbounded.

    Lib changes
    -----------

    usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/github-org-lib.bsh

      Default LOG_MAX_LEN to GHORG_MAX_DISPLAY_LEN (256 bytes) at lib
      source time using the same '[[ -v VAR ]] || VAR=...' idiom as the
      other lib env-var defaults. Operator can override by exporting
      LOG_MAX_LEN before invoking the tool. Per-call '${var:0:512}' bash
      slices in apply_code_security_config and policy_api_call remain as
      defense-in-depth and get re-clamped to LOG_MAX_LEN by
      sanitize-string.

    usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/github-policy-lib.bsh

      policy_api_call gains an optional 6th arg, body_var_name. When set,
      the response body is written into that caller-scope variable via
      'printf -v' on a 2xx (or extra_ok) success path. Cleared to ''
      on dry-run, warn, and ghorg_api error paths so callers can rely
      on "empty means no body to parse". Empty body_var_name (the
      default) skips body capture entirely.

      Asserts: body_var_name (when non-empty) must pass
      check_variable_name (R-140 defense-in-depth at the indirection
      site).

      _policy_upsert_ruleset switches from raw ghorg_api +
      status-check + warn duplication to policy_api_call with body
      capture for the GET-list step. The function body shrinks; the warn
      format becomes uniform with the rest of the lib.

    Tool changes
    ------------

    usr/bin/dm-github-org-policy

      apply_code_security_config refactored to use policy_api_call's body
      capture for the list and create paths. The function shrinks; the
      inline 'log warn ... ${list_body:0:512}' / '${create_body:0:512}'
      warn formatting is replaced by the lib's standard form. Operator-
      visible 'created code-security configuration id=N' notice
      preserved (the generic 'ok:' line is set at call time before .id
      is parsed, so the id-bearing line is logged separately).

      POST-id validation matches the PATCH-id path: regex + length cap
      before the id flows into the attach + defaults URLs.

    usr/bin/dm-github-fork-sync

      Source github-org-lib.bsh in addition to log_run_die.sh + has.sh
      (R-082: source every helper-scripts file used directly; do not
      rely on transitive sourcing). The lib pulls in the LOG_MAX_LEN
      default so the wrapper's own log lines get the same cap as the
      spawned github-org-fork child.

    usr/bin/github-org-fork

      check_variable_name asserts at the two caller-named-variable
      indirection sites: combine_alt's nameref ('local -n list_ref="$1"')
      and fork_main_build_repo_set's printf -v
      ('printf -v "${set_name}[${repo_name}]" ...'). Both current call
      sites pass literal identifiers, so the asserts never fire in
      practice; they tighten the contract so a future caller cannot
      pass garbage and get a non-obvious error mid-call.

    Tests
    -----

    Suite goes from 7 to 17 mock-API tests. New tests + fixtures fill
    the coverage gap on the body-capture refactor and on every code
    path the prior suite had only smoke-exercised via dry-run:

      ci/tests/test_policy_api_call_body_capture.sh
        Unit-style. Sources both libs, calls policy_api_call directly
        with the 6th-arg body capture, asserts:
          1. captured variable populated on 200 success
          2. captured variable cleared on dry-run short-circuit
          3. 5-arg form (no body capture) still works unchanged
          4. policy_warn_seen stays 0 across only-2xx calls
          5. captured cleared AND policy_warn_seen flipped on warn path
          6. invalid body_var_name (check_variable_name reject) returns
             non-zero without bumping policy_warn_seen

      ci/tests/test_dm_apply.sh
        Full-stack dm-github-org-policy --apply against fixtures.
        Walks org settings, members policy, code-security config (list /
        create / attach / default), branch + tag rulesets, per-repo
        PATCH. Indirectly validates body-capture end-to-end via the
        create -> attach handoff (broken capture would feed empty
        existing_id into the attach URL, miss its fixture, trip rc != 0).

      ci/tests/test_dm_personal_apply.sh
        dm-github-personal-policy --apply --verbose. Only test that
        exercises _policy_upsert_ruleset with scope=repo (the repo-level
        ruleset upsert) AND the 5th-arg extra_ok parameter (Pages
        DELETE -> 404 = "no Pages site" must NOT trip a warn). Two
        fixture repos in scope, one with Pages 204 and one with Pages
        404, hitting both branches of the extra_ok glob.

      ci/tests/test_dm_github_token_test.sh
        dm-github-token-test against /user (existing fixture) and
        /rate_limit (new fixture). Pins the .login extraction +
        rate-limit jq filter + the low-remaining warn threshold (4500 >
        100, no warn).

      ci/tests/test_dm_fork_sync_dryrun.sh
        dm-github-fork-sync --dry-run end-to-end. Wrapper sources the
        full lib chain and spawns github-org-fork once per SOURCE_ORGS
        entry; this test pins both the wrapper-level log notice headers
        AND the spawned tool's per-repo dry-run output. New per-source
        fixtures for Kicksecure + Whonix.

      ci/tests/test_fork_apply.sh
        github-org-fork --apply against fixtures. Walks fork creation
        (POST /repos/{src}/{repo}/forks for repos missing on target),
        collision detection (parent.full_name lookup), configure_one
        (PATCH + PUT settings), and sync_one (merge-upstream).

    ci/fixtures/ gains 33 entries covering the write endpoints
    (PUT/POST/PATCH/DELETE) the apply paths hit, plus per-source-org
    fixtures for the fork-sync wrapper test and per-repo response
    shapes for the github-org-fork apply test.

    Remaining gaps not in this PR
    -----------------------------

    github-org-clone --apply and github-org-push --apply exec git as a
    subprocess; mocking that requires shell-function overrides which
    agents/security.md flags as fragile (defeated by 'command git' or
    absolute-path invocations, and proves only that the mock fires, not
    the production code path).

    Style
    -----

    ASCII only (R-001) in code and commit message. Strict-mode quintet
    on every new test (R-010). 'rc=0; out=$(cmd) || rc=$?' for
    exit-code capture (R-011). 'log'/'die' from log_run_die.sh, not
    ad-hoc printf/exit (R-040, R-110). Direct sourcing of every
    helper-scripts file used (R-082). Long flags throughout (R-060).
    '--' end-of-options where supported (R-062). check_variable_name
    asserts at indirection sites (R-140 belt-and-suspenders).

