    -> '${dist_build_$&:-}"' on lines 288, 293, 302, 306, 310.

commit e300a634159b4df4c181b2620d70725a4e7898ef
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu May 7 09:34:01 2026 +0000

    fix(dm-prepare-release): protect dist_build_* derefs under nounset

    35 'if [ "${dist_build_X}" = "true" ]' guards across the file
    dereferenced their var without the ':-' default-value form. With
    'set -o nounset' (default), any --target / --flavor combination
    that did not happen to set that specific var aborted dm-prepare-
    release with '<var>: unbound variable'. Most callers only set ONE
    of the dist_build_* target booleans (parse-cmd in derivative-maker
    exports exactly one based on '--target X'), so most of these
    checks tripped on an unrelated target every build.

    Convert all 35 to the ':-' default-value form. No behaviour change
    for any case where the var is set; unset cases now compare ""
    against "true" (false), exactly the "skip-this-target" branch the
    guard already intends. Bash style guide R-010 (nounset is
    mandatory; consumers handle unset).

    Vars touched (all in 'if' guards of the same shape):
      dist_build_virtualbox        x2
      dist_build_qcow2             x8
      dist_build_raw               x8
      dist_build_utm               x1
      dist_build_iso               x1
      dist_build_windows_installer x2
      dist_build_installer_dist    x2
      dist_build_source_archive    x10

commit 045d164499595329db2b45d67fd0f8abbda5a5b1
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Wed May 6 21:05:27 2026 +0000

    ci: inline canonical repo literal in job-level if (env context unavailable)

    GitHub Actions does not expose the env context in job-level if
    expressions (only github, inputs, needs, vars are available there);
    referencing env.CANONICAL_REPO produced "Unrecognized named-value:
    'env'" and prevented the workflows from loading. Inline the literal
    'Kicksecure/developer-meta-files' in the if and drop the now-unused
    workflow-level env block. Caught by actionlint.

