commit ef46b6f65db1c76785f23e12ab02d5b33d6d7628
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 19:03:23 2026 +0000

    agents/: restructure bash style guide as flat-numbered R-NNN rules

    Rewrites agents/bash-style-guide.md as a flat numbered list of
    ~50 rules (R-001 through R-140), with each rule in the form:

       **R-NNN: <one-line statement>**

       Why: <one-paragraph rationale>

       <optional code example>

    Skim the bold lines to audit a diff; read the Why for context.
    Lets reviewers cite R-NNN in commits / PR replies and (eventually)
    makes "did this commit cite the rule it relaxes" a CI gate.

    Splits project-specific rules out into agents/github-org-tools.md
    under G-NNN. The bash guide now strictly covers portable bash;
    github-org-* / dm-* tool-family conventions
    (ghorg_validate_name / ghorg_safe_print boundary, mode-flag
    contract, policy_warn_seen pattern, mock-API test conventions)
    live in github-org-tools.md. Cross-references between the two
    are explicit (R-140 abstract -> G-001 through G-004 concrete).

    Adds agents/pre-push-checklist.md, capturing the user's existing
    checklist plus items that bit me during PR #7:

       - shellcheck --external-sources for cross-file SC2317 catches
       - arr=() init under nounset before any access
       - 'rc=0; out=$(cmd) || rc=$?' instead of toggling errexit
       - case-pattern interpolations need "${x}" quoting
       - tests capture combined output via 2>&1 (printf->log moved
         everything to stderr)
       - drop '^prefix' anchored greps; use --fixed-strings substrings
       - reinstall ALL changed binaries before running the suite,
         not just the file you touched
       - run the FULL test suite, not just the test for one file
       - re-trace data flow end-to-end after any scope/signature
         refactor

    Each checklist item cites the underlying R-NNN / G-NNN rule.

    Doc rewrite only - no code changes.

