commit 2c165123d68e4c864379720c270a211e9450b2bc
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 16:35:03 2026 +0000

    dm-github-personal-policy: init positional=() before policy_tool_init

    Codex P2: policy_tool_init reads '\${#positional[@]}' under
    'set -o nounset', so a caller without positional=() initialized
    crashes with 'positional: unbound variable' instead of the
    intended 'die 64' usage path.

    The previous code (before a4f5914) declared positional=() right
    before policy_parse_mode_args; the policy_tool_init refactor
    dropped it because the rest of the state-init block already
    covered mode/dry_run/verbose/mode_set. Add it back alongside
    those, matching dm-github-policy.

    Reproduced and confirmed: 'dm-github-personal-policy --apply'
    (missing <username>) now exits 64 with the help block + the
    'expected exactly 1 positional argument(s)' message instead of
    unbound-variable.

