commit a4f5914643b115a09a4f7ddcdb6272fb02e03b20
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 16:29:04 2026 +0000

    github-policy-lib: add policy_tool_init wrapper

    Both apply tools repeated the same six-line postlude after parsing
    flags: positional-count check, mode-set check, ghorg_require_deps
    call, and policy_warn_seen=0. Move that into a single
    policy_tool_init helper in github-policy-lib.bsh, taking the
    expected positional count as its first arg.

    Caller boilerplate after this:

       policy_tool_init 0 "$@"   ## dm-github-policy   (no positional)
       policy_tool_init 1 "$@"   ## dm-github-personal-policy (<user>)

    The wrapper calls policy_parse_mode_args, post-checks via the
    caller-defined show_help / die, runs the dependency pre-flight,
    and zeroes the warn flag. Doc block in the lib lists the full set
    of helpers callers can use.

    ci/tests/test_shellcheck_clean.sh switched to '--external-sources'
    (short form '-x'). Without it, shellcheck does not follow the
    '# shellcheck source=' directive into github-policy-lib.bsh, so
    SC2317 fires on show_help in the apply tools (which is now only
    called indirectly from inside the lib). With --external-sources
    the cross-file usage is tracked correctly.

