commit bb37101b004b059861eab6d37cae579dd9cc42a1
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 16:13:25 2026 +0000

    github-policy-lib: accept extra ok status; pages 404 is not a warn

    Codex P2 caught: 'DELETE /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pages' returns 404
    when the repo has no Pages site, which is GitHub's documented
    "nothing to delete" response. policy_api_call previously treated
    every non-2xx as a warn, so a routine apply run against a backup-
    mirror account would set policy_warn_seen for every repo without
    Pages and exit non-zero even when everything else succeeded.

    policy_api_call grows an optional 5th arg: one extra HTTP status
    code to accept as success. The case statement quotes the expansion
    ("${extra_ok}") so bash treats it as a literal pattern rather than
    a glob (SC2254). Single-value only - case-pattern expansion does
    not interpret '|' inside the substituted string as alternation, so
    pipe-separated forms would silently fail to match.

    dm-github-personal-policy step 5 (Pages DELETE) passes '404' as
    the extra-ok status. The existing comment is updated to explain
    why the lib treats 404 as success instead of warn.

    Codex P2 review point on PR #7.

commit 09ec964f77594e3a6239c337a08236e4b66997a0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 16:08:59 2026 +0000

    github-policy-lib + dm-github-{,personal-}policy: drop tempfile, use policy_warn_seen var

    Simpler than the POLICY_WARN_FILE / mktemp / EXIT-trap / cleanup-
    function machinery. The lib's policy_api_call and ruleset-upsert
    helper now mutate ${policy_warn_seen} directly via bash dynamic
    scoping; the tool initializes it to 0 at top level and tests it
    '-eq 1' at exit. No per-call '|| policy_warn_seen=1' boilerplate
    needed - the lib does the assignment.

    dm-github-policy's per-repo loop drops the '&' / 'wait -n' pattern
    in favor of a plain sequential loop. With one org of ~12 repos and
    one PATCH per repo, the parallelism saved a couple of seconds at
    most; sequentializing lets the policy_warn_seen mutations from the
    lib propagate back to the tool's scope without a shared file. The
    unused POLICY_JOBS=4 const goes with it.

    dm-github-personal-policy was already sequential; same pattern,
    just initialize policy_warn_seen=0 at top and test at exit.

    _policy_mark_warn helper in the lib is gone (was only there to
    abstract the file-append). Doc block updated.

