    dm-github-personal-policy: refuse Organization accounts (P1 codex)

    ghorg_validate_name only checks the string format - both 'alice'
    and 'whonix' pass that step. Without an explicit account-type
    check, an operator who typed an org name by mistake would have the
    personal-mirror lockdown (Actions disabled, default-branch ruleset,
    tag ruleset, settings PATCH) applied to every public repo in that
    org. That is a high-blast-radius footgun on an apply run.

    Resolve the account type via ghorg_account_type (GET /users/{name})
    and bail out with exit 64 unless GitHub reports type=User. The
    refusal message names the offending type and points the operator
    at dm-github-policy as the org-side tool.

    ci/tests/test_dm_personal_refuses_org.sh: regression test that runs
    the tool against the existing org fixture (org-ai-assisted ->
    type=Organization) and asserts:
      - non-zero exit
      - refusal message names the type
      - no DRY-RUN: line slipped through (refusal happens before the
        per-repo loop starts)

