commit b0b165f1d95c85697d0499a970f3184e1fc66ca0
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 06:56:06 2026 +0000

    dm-github-personal-policy: add rulesets, secret-scan, settings cleanup

    Extend the per-repo lockdown to match the full attack surface raised
    in review:

    New per-repo settings:

    - Wiki / Projects / Discussions disabled. Single PATCH alongside the
      security_and_analysis change (one API call instead of three). Cuts
      wiki-vandalism-via-PR, projects-spam, discussions-spam abuse
      vectors. has_issues left untouched - issues are useful even on a
      backup mirror.

    - Secret scanning + push-protection enabled via security_and_analysis
      block in the same PATCH. Free for public repos. Push-protection
      blocks accidental commits of secrets at push time, before they hit
      the public mirror.

    - Pages site deletion via DELETE /repos/{owner}/{repo}/pages.
      Idempotent in spirit (404 on no-site is benign warn). Cuts
      accidental-publication surface. Note: this is a one-shot cleanup,
      not a permanent gate - any future Pages workflow run will recreate
      the site.

    - Branch ruleset (per-repo) on the default branch: block force-push,
      block deletion, require signed commits. bypass_actors=[]. Mirror
      of dm-github-policy's org-level branch ruleset, scoped to one repo
      via /repos/{owner}/{repo}/rulesets.

    - Tag ruleset (per-repo) on all tags: block deletion, block
      re-pointing, require signed tags. Same bypass_actors=[].

    New helper:

    - upsert_repo_ruleset() - idempotent find-by-name then PUT-update or
      POST-create. Mirror of dm-github-policy's upsert_org_ruleset.
      Validates the API-derived id via [0-9]+ + GHORG_MAX_ID_LEN cap
      before interpolating into the PUT path (audit-checklist rule:
      identifier sink).

    Deliberately commented out (with rationale inline):

    - Vulnerability alerts (PUT /vulnerability-alerts).
    - Dependabot security updates (PUT /automated-security-fixes).

    Reason: the personal account is a backup/mirror of org-side work
    (Kicksecure, Whonix). Orgs may delete repos for brevity; the
    personal account preserves history. Enabling Dependabot here would
    duplicate notifications already raised on the canonical org-side
    repo. The code paths are present but commented; uncomment when a
    repo becomes canonical on the personal account.

    show_help updated to list every new setting.

