commit 815e087e4ad131ae6ecf4280b90de406ae2834d2
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 00:34:27 2026 +0000

    github-org-* / dm-github-*: reject conflicting modes; document --apply

    Codex review of 6a7e121 raised four issues:

    1. P1 (dm-github-policy mode validator): the post-parse check only
       confirmed that *some* mode flag was set, so 'dm-github-policy
       --audit --apply' or '--dry-run --audit' was accepted with
       last-flag-wins, silently flipping audit to apply (or vice versa).
       Contradicts the "exactly one" contract printed in --help and
       error text.

       Fix: each mode arm guards on '${mode_set} -eq 0' before setting
       it; second mode flag dies 64 with 'conflicting mode flags;
       specify exactly one of ...'. Applied to all six tools.

       Verified locally:
         --apply              -> OK
         --dry-run            -> OK
         (empty)              -> die 64 'missing mode'
         --apply --dry-run    -> die 64 'conflicting mode flags'
         --dry-run --apply    -> die 64 'conflicting mode flags'
         --apply --apply      -> die 64 'conflicting mode flags'

    2-4. P2 (github-org-{clone,fork,push} help text): the parser change
         in 6a7e121 added --apply but show_help still listed only
         --dry-run, so any operator following --help for a normal
         (non-dry-run) invocation hit a mode error.

         Fix:
           - Usage line: 'Usage (one mode flag is required - no implicit
             default):' with both --apply and --dry-run forms shown
             explicitly.
           - Options block: --apply documented next to --dry-run.

    dm-github-policy and dm-github-personal-policy already had their help
    updated in 6a7e121; dm-github-fork-sync's help was updated too. The
    gap was on the three github-org-* tools.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01U5dqsVj1msLQMiCemkuddP

commit 6a7e121d8a721bc3648eddebcf8fa845bb1cb769
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Mon May 4 00:26:23 2026 +0000

    github-org-* / dm-github-*: require explicit mode flag, no implicit default

    Per the project's "no implicit default for mutating tools" rule:
    running any of these scripts without a mode flag previously fell
    through to APPLY semantics, mutating org/repo state under "what the
    operator forgot to type" - the kind of footgun that can't ship.

    Affected tools (all on this PR's surface):

      dm-github-policy           --apply | --dry-run | --audit
      dm-github-personal-policy  --apply | --dry-run | --audit
      dm-github-fork-sync        --apply | --dry-run
      github-org-fork            --apply | --dry-run
      github-org-clone           --apply | --dry-run
      github-org-push            --apply | --dry-run

    Each tool now:
      - tracks mode_set=0 and only sets it inside an explicit flag arm
      - errors with 'specify exactly one of --apply / ...' + show_help
        if mode_set != 1 after the parser

    dm-github-fork-sync also pre-checks mode and refuses up-front so the
    error names the wrapper rather than the spawned github-org-fork.

    Help text updated to make the requirement visible at the top of
    each Usage block:

      Usage (one mode flag is required - no implicit default):

    This is a breaking change for any existing automation that called
    these tools without flags. By design - the previous implicit-apply
    behaviour was the bug.

