Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 2 18:54:08 2026 +0000

    dm-fork-sync: --include-forks in POLICY_FLAGS

    Kicksecure has ~13 repos that are forks of upstream projects
    (grml-debootstrap, tirdad, bindp, calamares-settings-debian,
    grub-live, lxqt-wayland-session, mediawiki-shell, privleap,
    ro-mode-init, sandbox-app-launcher, sysmaint-panel, tor-ctrl,
    qubes-template-whonix). github-org-fork defaults to skipping forks
    (GET /orgs/{org}/repos with .fork == false filter), which left
    those out of the org-ai-assisted mirror.

    Add --include-forks to POLICY_FLAGS so the mirror covers the full
    Kicksecure surface. The new mirror entries become second-level
    forks (parent = Kicksecure's fork, grandparent = the original
    upstream).

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01U5dqsVj1msLQMiCemkuddP

commit 4acea3ec3ca5ba268ba688c9f2d77f378646fa46
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat May 2 18:47:30 2026 +0000

    github-org-fork / dm-fork-sync: best-effort configure, --debug, token-test

    Three independent fixes/additions for dm-fork-sync ergonomics:

    1. github-org-fork main(): make the post-fork configure loop best-
       effort. Previously a single check_collision or configure_one
       failure (return 1) tripped errexit and aborted the whole run -
       killing every subsequent repo's configure AND every subsequent
       source org the caller had queued. The most common transient
       cause is async fork creation: GitHub's POST /forks returns 202
       before the new repo's Actions subsystem accepts
       PUT /repos/{owner}/{repo}/actions/permissions, so the first
       configure pass on a fresh fork can 404/403. With '|| true' in
       the loop, a re-run picks the failures up idempotently. Brief
       comment explains the rationale inline.

    2. --debug flag (passes through dm-fork-sync to github-org-fork):
       sets 'set -x' in both. Previously only 'bash -x dm-fork-sync'
       traced the wrapper; the spawned github-org-fork ran without
       tracing, hiding most of the interesting work. Now:
         dm-fork-sync --debug
       propagates the flag to every github-org-fork invocation.
       github-org-fork itself also accepts --debug standalone.

    3. dm-github-token-test: trivial helper that calls /user and
       /rate_limit and prints login + remaining quota. Useful as a
       pre-flight before dm-fork-sync / dm-github-policy --apply.
       Fails closed with a clear error when the token is missing /
       invalid / over quota.

    https://claude.ai/code/session_01U5dqsVj1msLQMiCemkuddP

