commit a06e4b67d5a1d61554f09bf26ee4e08536d9f7bf
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 19:32:01 2026 +0000

    github-org tools + dm-github-policy + dm-fork-sync: full add + polish

    New surface for managing the assisted-by-ai GitHub org, plus the CI
    scripts and workflows that exercise it.

    Tools (usr/bin/):
    - github-org-clone, github-org-fork, github-org-push: per-repo and
      per-org clone, fork, and push primitives. Parser guards on every
      --option N pair, ghorg_validate_name on CLI-derived owners,
      --jobs bounded 1..200, is_whole_number checks via strings.bsh.
    - dm-github-policy: idempotent org policy applier (apply / audit /
      dry-run) covering 2FA, members lacking 2FA, fork-PR approval,
      workflow GITHUB_TOKEN permissions, allowed_actions, code-security
      configuration upsert + attach + default, and branch + tag
      rulesets.
    - dm-fork-sync: sync forks from upstream orgs into the mirror org.

    Library (usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/):
    - github-org-lib.bsh: shared GHORG_API client. Sources strings.bsh,
      log_run_die.sh, has.sh from helper-scripts directly (no transitive
      reliance). Hostile-API hardening: GHORG_MAX_PAGES, GHORG_MAX_REDIRS,
      GHORG_MAX_ID_LEN, GIT_LFS_SKIP_SMUDGE=1, git clone --config
      protocol.file.allow=never / protocol.ext.allow=never. Token
      handling: length cap + check_is_alpha_numeric on GITHUB_TOKEN and
      on token-file content, fail closed when stat cannot read mode,
      fail closed when configured token invalid (refuse anonymous
      fallback). GHORG_API_VERSION env-overridable, default 2026-03-10
      after auditing the breaking-changes list against our endpoints.
      api_call accepts 200|201|202|204 (the attach POST returns 202).
      ?per_page=100 on the code-security and rulesets list endpoints.

    Workflows (.github/workflows/):
    - test-github-org-tools.yml: mock-API suite (8 tests) under CI=true.
    - live.yml: combined unauth probe + dm-github-policy --audit +
      --dry-run against org-ai-assisted, GET-only, manual dispatch,
      read-only PAT (GHORG_AUDIT_TOKEN secret).
    GitHub Actions sets CI=true automatically; no env: blocks needed.

    CI scripts (ci/):
    - install-helper-scripts.sh, install-genmkfile.sh: install upstream
      deps before mock + live runs.
    - live-probe-unauth.sh: smoke probe via the unauth rate-limit bucket.
    - test-github-org-tools.sh: orchestrate mock tests under tests/.
    - tests/test_*.sh: clone, fork, dm-audit, dm-dryrun, rate-limit-retry,
      shellcheck-clean, validate-name-rejects-attacks, plus
      include-private-user.

    Codex PR #5 keepers: parser guards, ghorg_validate_name on CLI-derived
    owners, --jobs bounds, token format check, is_whole_number from
    strings.bsh. Codex paranoia (HELPER_SCRIPTS_REF SHA pinning,
    SECURITY_REVIEW.md, 5 paranoia tests) deliberately not adopted; the
    stat-mock-via-shell-function technique is now codified in
    agents/security.md as something we don't carry.

    Agents docs (agents/):
    - bash-style-guide.md (canonical home for the org-wide style guide).
    - security.md: introduction + two threat models + comparison table +
      conclusion (CI/maintenance tooling vs derivative-maker production
      code; the production-code threat model lives in derivative-maker).
    - github-org-tools.md: tool-specific specifics (ghorg_validate_name,
      ghorg_safe_print, GHORG_MAX_*, audit checklist).
    - AGENTS.md: short index pointing into agents/.

    Style sweep (existing files): braced ${var} throughout, printf
    '%s\n' "..." style, local var1 var2 var3 at function top with blank
    line after, split case arms with ;; on its own line, safe-rm over
    rm, standalone trap functions, true "INFO: ..." debug-string null
    ops, jq/sed/tr -- end-of-options, single-quote-around-vars in error
    messages, log/die replaces ad-hoc printf '...' >&2; exit N, has from
    helper-scripts replaces command -v X >/dev/null 2>&1, # shellcheck
    source=/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/<file> over /dev/null. Trimmed
    AI-tell suffixes from error messages (; refusing X, ; aborting,
    parenthetical reasoning).

    dm-packaging-helper-script: pkg_claude_md_pointer_do auto-generates
    a minimal CLAUDE.md -> AGENTS.md redirect when packaged repos
    already have an AGENTS.md.

    github-org-set-fork-approval deleted - dm-github-policy --audit /
    --apply / --dry-run covers every use case.

