commit 8a83cb447d7a1fb6ae61ac0e7a4b8e393d5b5b3c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 09:55:39 2026 +0000

    style: quote interpolated values; [[ -v ]] for env defaults; JSON exception

    Three coordinated style refinements after the previous big sweep.

      * Single-quote-around-vars in error/warn/reject messages: every
        interpolated value that flows into a diagnostic string is now
        wrapped in single quotes, e.g. "error: '${path}' permissions are
        '${mode}', expected 600 or 400". A reader sees the exact byte
        boundary of the variable's value, including any leading or
        trailing whitespace, and "it's a variable" is unambiguous from
        the surrounding literal text. Applied across the lib (token
        file, validator, account_type, list_repos, repo_lookup,
        repo_parent, authenticated_user, retry warns) and across
        github-org-clone / -fork / -push / -set-fork-approval and
        dm-github-policy. test_set_fork_approval_user_refused.sh's
        grep needle is updated to match the new quoted phrasing.

      * Env-var defaults via "[[ -v VAR ]] || VAR=...": each tunable
        knob in github-org-lib.bsh now uses bash's "is set" test
        instead of the "${VAR:-default}" inline-default form. Keeps
        the assignment line scannable and surfaces the default value
        plainly. Applied to GHORG_API, GHORG_MAX_RETRIES,
        GHORG_MAX_BACKOFF_SECONDS, GHORG_MAX_PAGES, GHORG_MAX_REDIRS.

      * JSON-literal printf exception: ghorg_mock_dispatch's missing-
        fixture error body is a JSON string with embedded double
        quotes. The project-wide rule ("printf '%s\n' \"...\"") would
        require backslash-escaping every internal quote. The cleaner
        form for this case is the format-spec with %s placeholders -
        documented inline as the explicit exception to the rule.

    AI-Assisted

