commit 2a2129aa4c608ab6a9122e983b88365b688316aa
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 09:47:34 2026 +0000

    style: braced \${var}, split case arms, helper-scripts via env, MIRROR rename

    A coordinated style sweep across the AI-Assisted github-org-* /
    dm-github-policy / dm-fork-sync surface plus the CI scripts that
    exercise it.

      * Variable expansion: every "\$var" reference is now "\${var}".
        Easier to spot the boundary between identifier and surrounding
        text. Existing "\${var:-default}" forms are kept where they were
        needed for nounset safety; no new "\${var:-}" defaults were added.

      * Case arms: every multi-statement single-line case arm is split
        onto separate lines, with ";;" on its own line. Includes the
        main arg parsers in github-org-clone / -fork / -push /
        -set-fork-approval / dm-fork-sync / dm-github-policy plus the
        nested --actions / --workflow-perms case in github-org-fork and
        the status-code switches in ghorg_repo_lookup / fork_one /
        ghorg_validate_name's kind dispatch / ghorg_list_repos's
        account-type dispatch.

      * Helper-scripts source: github-org-clone now sources wc-test.sh
        via "\${HELPER_SCRIPTS_PATH:-}/usr/libexec/helper-scripts/...",
        matching the existing convention. Empty default = system
        install at /usr/libexec/helper-scripts/; an in-tree caller
        (e.g. derivative-maker running with helper-scripts as a
        submodule) can point at the submodule instead.

      * MIRROR rename: dm-packaging-helper-script's
        DM_GITHUB_TEST_MIRROR / DM_GITHUB_PROD_MIRROR pair collapses to
        a single DM_GITHUB_MIRROR='org-ai-assisted'. The org IS the
        production mirror; the previous "test mirror" framing was
        inaccurate. The deprecated assisted-by-ai personal-account
        remote is dropped from pkg_git_remotes_add since that account
        is being phased out (kept only for org-ai-assisted admin).

      * dm-fork-sync: MIRROR='org-ai-assisted' (was assisted-by-ai),
        SOURCE_ORGS=( 'Kicksecure' 'Whonix' ) (production list active).
        Help text and header comments updated to match.

      * Lib globals: each environment-overridable knob now has its own
        standalone comment block followed by the assignment then a
        blank line. GHORG_MAX_REPO_NAME_LEN / _USER_LOGIN_LEN /
        _DISPLAY_LEN / _RETRIES / _BACKOFF_SECONDS / _PAGES / _REDIRS /
        _ID_LEN are all visually separated.

    AI-Assisted

commit c592c7aaee1a375a77daf61b824b3271a2cc5da4
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 09:32:55 2026 +0000

    style: globals at top, blank line after locals, no \n in printf format

    Two consistent style changes across the github-org-* / dm-* tools and
    their CI scripts:

      * Globals consolidated at the top of github-org-lib.bsh in a single
        GLOBALS block: GHORG_API, GHORG_MAX_REPO_NAME_LEN /
        GHORG_MAX_USER_LOGIN_LEN / GHORG_MAX_DISPLAY_LEN, GHORG_MAX_RETRIES /
        GHORG_MAX_BACKOFF_SECONDS, GHORG_MAX_PAGES / GHORG_MAX_REDIRS /
        GHORG_MAX_ID_LEN, ghorg_account_type_cache, and
        ghorg_authenticated_user_cached. Previously they were sprinkled
        throughout the file in front of the function that first used them;
        now a reader sees the full state surface at a glance. Each function
        that uses them comments back-references to the globals block.

      * Blank line after every "local" declaration block, and a blank
        line after the parameter-assignment block before logic begins.
        Matches the dm-packaging-helper-script convention. Applies to
        every function in the suite (~25 functions touched).

      * No extra "\n" in printf format strings. "printf '\n%s\n' ..."
        rewrites to a separate "printf '%s\n' \"\"" for the blank line
        plus the actual content printf. Multi-line content where each
        line is logically distinct uses one printf per line; multi-line
        content that reads as a single block (e.g. skip-with-URL-pointer
        messages) uses a single double-quoted string with embedded
        newlines so only one open/close quote pair is required. The
        summary block in dm-github-policy main() is the canonical
        "one-printf-per-line" example.

    AI-Assisted

commit 116d9fd1741f55717c06b50ccb1d7f47faa30f82
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri May 1 08:47:03 2026 +0000

    hostile-API hardening: pagination, redirect, id-length, LFS, git protos

    Five additional defenses against a compromised or hostile GitHub
    REST endpoint, on top of the existing ghorg_validate_name allowlist
    and ghorg_safe_print sanitize-string layer:

      * GHORG_MAX_PAGES (default 100) caps pagination depth in
        ghorg_list_repos. Without it, a server returning 100 repos per
        page forever would keep the pager loop alive until OOM. The cap
        fires with a clear warn line so the operator can investigate
        rather than silently truncating the result set.

      * --max-redirs GHORG_MAX_REDIRS (default 5) bounds curl's redirect
        chain. Modern curl strips Authorization on cross-host redirect
        by default, so the token does not leak; this cap is for the
        request URL itself (which carries the org name and path) being
        bounced through attacker-controlled hosts.

      * GHORG_MAX_ID_LEN (20) caps the byte length of any "numeric" id
        extracted from a body before it is interpolated into a URL path.
        The existing ^[0-9]+$ regex would otherwise accept a 10000-digit
        string. Applied to ruleset id and code-security configuration id
        in dm-github-policy.

      * GIT_LFS_SKIP_SMUDGE=1 in github-org-clone's git clone env
        prevents the LFS smudge filter from auto-fetching attacker-
        chosen objects when an upstream's .gitattributes points binary
        files at LFS. Operators who want LFS payloads can pre-set the
        env var to anything other than 1.

      * git clone --config protocol.file.allow=never and
        protocol.ext.allow=never block the file:// and ext:: helper
        protocols, which have been used in past CVEs to read local
        files or run shell commands on clone when a hostile upstream
        redirects a sub-fetch.

    The threat-model header in github-org-lib.bsh now lists every
    resource cap and clone-time hardening so future readers see the
    defenses inline with the validate-at-sinks / sanitize-at-display
    boundary.

    AI-Assisted

commit 8506b20647d18d086c4f8911d2c426cd2535806c
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 30 23:26:47 2026 +0000

    project-wide style sweep: printf, jq/sed/tr --, safe-rm, wc-test

    Mechanical sweep across the github-org-* / dm-github-policy /
    dm-packaging-helper-script tools and their CI scripts:

      * printf style: every "printf 'TEXT %s\n' \"\$var\"" is rewritten as
        "printf '%s\n' \"TEXT \$var\"". The format string is now a fixed
        literal in every call; variables only appear inside the data
        string, never inside the format. printf '%s\r\n' is used in the
        rate-limit fixtures where CRLF is required structurally.

      * end-of-options separators: jq, sed, tr now pass "--" before the
        filter / script / set arg. Same defensive idiom we already used
        on git, grep, head, tail.

      * "true MSG" debug: bare "true" placeholders inside ghorg_api retry
        case arms are now "true 'INFO: ...'" so the comment text shows up
        in xtrace, matching the dm-packaging-helper-script convention.

      * trap nounset safety: documented in the trap-target function
        header that hdr_file (etc.) is initialized BEFORE the trap is
        registered, so the bare "$hdr_file" reference is safe under
        "set -o nounset" and no "${hdr_file:-}" default is needed (using
        one would mask a real init-order regression).

      * safe-rm everywhere: the four "rm" calls left in the suite (lib
        trap target, dm-github-policy trap target, ci/test-github-org-
        tools.sh per-test cleanup, and the two ci/tests trap targets)
        now call safe-rm with long flags (--force / --recursive). The
        apt install lists in policy-live.yml and test-github-org-tools.yml
        pick up the safe-rm package.

      * wc-test.sh sourced before wc: github-org-clone now sources
        /usr/libexec/helper-scripts/wc-test.sh up front so a broken wc
        binary fails loudly rather than silently producing an empty
        line count. wc -l rewritten as wc --lines.

      * dm-packaging-helper-script: the inline "assisted-by-ai" and
        "org-ai-assisted" strings I added in the previous round are now
        DM_GITHUB_PROD_MIRROR and DM_GITHUB_TEST_MIRROR readonly vars
        declared near the top of the script. The pkg_git_remotes_add /
        set_batch_current_package_remote_list bodies reference the vars
        instead of repeating the literal.

    AI-Assisted

