commit 15eb9b93d06c3f83b8eee8fd513e71f53ac3e8cf
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 30 22:49:15 2026 +0000

    github-org-* + dm-github-policy: style + threat-model polish

    Across the github-org-* / dm-github-policy / dm-packaging-helper-script
    surface and the CI scripts that exercise it:

      * printf style: command substitutions previously inlined as printf
        arguments are now hoisted to a named variable on a preceding line.
        Reads better and avoids burying the substitution.

      * local declarations: per-function locals are declared on a single
        "local var1 var2 var3" line at the top, then assigned. Drops the
        "local x=$(cmd)" pattern, which masks cmd's exit code because
        local always returns 0. Trivial assignments such as "local i=0"
        are kept inline.

      * Bot/test mirror as variables: the inline "assisted-by-ai" and
        "org-ai-assisted" strings in dm-packaging-helper-script are now
        DM_GITHUB_PROD_MIRROR and DM_GITHUB_TEST_MIRROR readonly vars
        declared near the top of the script. dm-fork-sync and
        dm-github-policy already had MIRROR / SOURCE_ORGS / ORGS at top.

      * Standalone trap functions: every "trap '<inline cmd>' <SIG>" is
        now "trap <named_function> <SIG>" with the function defined in
        the same file. Auditable as a callable, not a quoted snippet.

      * sanitize-string audit: every jq-extracted scalar that flows to
        a terminal now passes through ghorg_safe_print first (allowed_actions,
        enabled_repositories, PAT counts, webhook counts, install_line).
        A new THREAT MODEL block at the top of github-org-lib.bsh
        documents the "validate at identifier sinks, sanitize at display
        sinks" boundary and explains why we don't sanitize the raw body
        (it must be parsed by jq first).

      * NUL-delimited find: github-org-push discovers candidate clones
        via "find ... -print0 | sort --zero-terminated" and reads them
        with "read -d ''", so dirnames containing odd bytes survive.

      * Long option names: declare -gA -> declare -g -A; sort -u ->
        sort --unique. shellcheck/Bash long forms preferred everywhere
        they are documented.

      * end-of-options "--": stat invocations now pass -- before the
        file path so an attacker-controlled XDG_CONFIG_HOME path that
        happens to start with "-" cannot be mistaken for a flag.

      * Quoted reserved-name patterns: ".|..|.git" in case statements
        is now "'.'|'..'|'.git'" (and the "-*" / "*..*" arms gained the
        same explicit quoting). Defensive even though dot is not a
        glob char in case patterns.

      * Replaced ":" null-command with "true" in github-org-lib.bsh
        (while-true loop, retry case arms, hdr_file truncation). Easier
        to read at a glance than the colon idiom.

      * Documented ghorg_filter_names empty-pattern semantics: empty =
        "no filter on this side" by intent, scoped to repo-name filtering
        where include='' / exclude='' is the natural CLI default; not a
        generic security filter.

    AI-Assisted

