commit 9efa3ee727f0498a3f8edcb6e609448523a18366
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sun Apr 26 08:37:56 2026 +0000

    shellcheck-clean repo, address PR #1 feedback, harden git, fix bugs

    PR #1 review feedback (ERR trap nounset safety):
    - dm-git-commit-checkout-latest, dm-git-tag-checkout-latest: source
      help-steps/pre BEFORE installing the build_all_error_handler ERR
      trap, so an early failure no longer fires the trap with unset
      ${red}/${bold}/${reset}.
    - dm-paypal-wiki-templates-create: defaults the color expansions
      inside build_all_error_handler since this script never sources
      color-variable definitions.

    shellcheck cleanup:
    - Add .shellcheckrc with the project's existing exclusion list plus
      SC2154 (vars from sourced help-steps/* files) and SC1091 (sources
      outside the repo).
    - Replace bare \$BASH_SOURCE with \${BASH_SOURCE[0]} and \"\$@\" with
      \$* in info/error strings repo-wide (SC2128/SC2145).
    - misc/commit-list: \$(basename \$(pwd)) -> \$(basename \"\$PWD\").
    - dm-check-mirrors: drop dead self-assignment of mirror_item.
    - dm-check-unicode: array expansion in printf string uses [*];
      switch missing-newline filter loop from for-over-string (split on
      whitespace) to while-read.
    - dm-get-tor-from-tpo-repo: per-line SC2037,SC2211 disable for the
      bash VAR=val command-prefix form; add -r to read.
    - dm-packaging-helper-script: convert pkg_git_branch_fetch_all to
      use an array; guard target_cmd=\"\${1:-}\" and arg_list[0]:- in
      main(); replace echo with printf; defensive declare -A name=();
      remove text_lower_case dead local; document internal_git_diff
      exit-128 path; pkg_compat_delete idempotent (|| true); bare
      return -> return 0 in three call sites.
    - dm-paypal-wiki-templates-create, dm-upload-canary,
      dm-upload-repository: read -r.
    - dm-prepare-release: \${FUNCNAME[0]} explicit index; \${arr[*]} in
      string contexts; per-line SC2089/SC2090 disable for TAR_OPTIONS
      (tar parses the embedded quotes itself); guard 0-files-matched
      case in the VirtualBox-*.exe glob counter; verify_cmd_signinfy
      threshold matches sign_cmd_signify (1000 MB, was 100 MB); drop
      dead binary_image_text_vbox_temp setup.
    - dm-qemu-amd64-bios, dm-qemu-amd64-efi, dm-qemu-arm64-efi: pass
      the drive file as \$1 instead of broken file=\$@ concatenation.
    - dm-replace-list: drop useless \$(echo \"...\"); switch the inner
      read loop's input feed from printf '%s\\n' to printf '%s' so the
      trailing-newline + appended-newline combination does not yield
      an empty trailing line that trips the empty-line guard.
    - dm-resign-canary: forward \"\$@\" to sanity_tests; guard \${3:-}
      in sign_cmd_signify / verify_cmd_signinfy; add -- before file
      argument on two sq verify calls.
    - dm-shellcheck-wrapper: convert opts to an array; while-read +
      -print0 (handles spaces); shebang check uses head -n 1; -r on
      read; drop a duplicate --exclude.
    - dm-tor-update-repository: fix two (( arr = 0 )) assignments that
      were meant to be == comparisons.
    - dm-virtualbox-installer-exe-verify-windows: same 0-files
      guard as dm-prepare-release.
    - dm-virtualbox-test-vm: vm_is_running_test now matches the full
      quoted name + uuid prefix via grep -F (handles spaces in VM
      names); wait_vm_shutdown timer starts before the loop instead of
      inside; vmname_with_quotes single-quote -> double-quote escape
      bug; vboxmanage_sudo_wrapper uses \$password instead of literal
      changeme.
    - dm-virtualbox-update-local-and-wiki-links: initialise
      regex_result=\"\" so the no-match path doesn't trip nounset.
    - dm-upload-images: \"_list_list\" typo -> \"_list\"; guard
      sleep_seconds; switch the per-retry sleep to a linear backoff
      computed from attempts_counter so the value cannot leak across
      upload_files invocations.
    - dm-upload-repository: initialise rsync_dry_run_maybe in main().
    - dm-bump-derivative-maker-version: drop the extra make_ prefix
      on genmkfile deb-uachl-commit-changelog.

    End-of-options markers (--):
    - Repo-wide for cp, mv, rm, mkdir, touch, tee, cat, chmod, git
      add / git rm / git checkout file form, dirname, basename,
      pushd, cd, command -v, xargs-bash, and the embedded shell in
      qvm-run / tar.
    - dm-get-tor-from-tpo-repo: drop the unnecessary `env` prefix; the
      bash VAR=val command-prefix form is fine.

    Git name-collision hardening:
    - git checkout BRANCH -> git switch BRANCH (only switches branches,
      cannot resolve to a same-named tag or pathspec).
    - git checkout FETCH_HEAD -> git switch --detach FETCH_HEAD.
    - All variable-derived refs use refs/heads/, refs/remotes/<remote>/
      or refs/tags/<tag> form so a tag named the same as a branch
      cannot be substituted in.
    - Push uses explicit src:dst refspec
      (refs/heads/X:refs/heads/X / refs/tags/X:refs/tags/X).

    Strict shell options:
    - Apply set -o errexit / nounset / pipefail / errtrace and shopt
      -s inherit_errexit consistently to all shell scripts.

    Reusable parallel-wait helper:
    - New usr/libexec/developer-meta-files/parallel.bsh exposes
      dm_parallel_wait NAME, which takes the name of an associative
      array { pid => label } via bash nameref, loops over wait -n -p
      VAR (bash >= 5.1), and reports each failed background job by
      label. Defensively resets done_pid before each wait because
      wait -n -p UNSETS the var when no child is left to reap.
    - dm-push uses it; failed pushes are reported by label
      (\"branch master -> github-kicksecure\") rather than \"at least
      one push failed\".
    - dm-packaging-helper-script's wait_for_git_processes hook uses it
      too; pkg_git_fetch_remotes / pkg_git_branch_fetch_all /
      pkg_git_push_tags / pkg_git_push_remotes record { pid => label }
      into the global git_pid_label associative array. The previous
      string-accumulator / wait \$git_pid_list_str pattern only ever
      surfaced the LAST pid's exit status; failures elsewhere were
      silently dropped. The serialization wait inside pkg_git_push_
      remotes is gone too, so pushes for one repo run in parallel.

    Other:
    - Replace echo with printf '%s\\n' (or printf '%s' / printf '\\n')
      so flag-stripping and escape-interpretation differences across
      bash versions / shells cannot mangle output.
    - dm-upgrade-from-local-repository: drop the
      /run/package_manager_lock touch / rm pair (no longer required).
    - qubes-mount-dev-xvdi: test -w /mnt/disk (the directory) instead
      of /mnt/disk/testfile (which would have required a sentinel
      file to pre-exist).
    - dm-tbb-update / dm-virtualbox-update-local-and-wiki-links:
      print the path of the leftover mktemp temp files on exit
      rather than deleting them (developer review aid).
    - dm-interactive-chroot-raw: fix typo'd error_handler_interactive-
      raw -> error_handler_interactive-chroot-raw inside the inner
      trap.
    - dm-mount-vdi: switch the .vdi find from a string capture (which
      silently produced a newline-separated path when more than one
      match existed) to an array with explicit zero/multiple-match
      checks.
    - dm-apt-get-wrapper-test: capture apt-get exit code via
      || apt_get_exit_code=\$?; the previous \$? read was racy under
      set -e.
    - dm-reprepro-wrapper: use error \"...\" for the not-found branch
      (was true \"ERROR: ...\"; exit 1, silent unless -x); drop the
      spurious \", ok.\" from the checksum-mismatch error message.
    - dm-packaging-helper-script::pkg_git_packages_git_log_writer:
      use \${derivative_maker_source_code_dir} (not hardcoded
      /home/user/derivative-maker/) when stripping PWD prefix.
    - dm-unmount-vdi / dm-unmount-vdi-force: rm -r -- form.
    - dm-packaging-helper-script::generate_announcement: header_text
      is now declared local; fix misleading 6-space indentation.
    - TODO comments: dm-rsync-test exithandler dependency; dm-upload-
      images list-vs-list_list iter naming; dm-virtualbox-test-vm
      benchmark_time_start naming alignment with derivative-maker;
      dm-install-from-local-repository -kde flavor coverage and
      package-name suffix consistency; interactive read prompts in
      dm-timesanitycheck-update / dm-tbb-update / dm-get-tor-from-tpo-
      repo.

