commit 58c2a7d1d864bbac398ced033ce180ad6bbc17b1
Author: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date:   Sat Apr 25 12:26:11 2026 +0000

    scripts: enforce strict shell options repo-wide

    Apply the canonical strict-mode block to every shell script in the
    repo (the pre-existing dangerous-scripts/dev_clearnet is effectively
    disabled with `exit 0` at the top and is intentionally untouched):

        set -o errexit
        set -o nounset
        set -o pipefail
        set -o errtrace
        shopt -s inherit_errexit

    Most scripts already had at least `set -e`; this normalizes them.

    Targeted nounset compatibility fixes applied where the new options
    would have surfaced an unbound variable at runtime:

    - dm-prepare-release: guard TAR_OPTIONS, XZ_OPT, DEBEMAIL; drop the
      obsolete inner set -o nounset / set +o nounset workaround inside
      signatures_create.
    - dm-packaging-helper-script: guard the associative-array probes in
      internal_descr_writer and pkg_descr_merger; guard target_cmd=\$1
      and arg_list[0] in main() so the no-arg path actually reaches its
      empty-arg check.
    - dm-resign-canary: guard DEBEMAIL in sanity_tests().
    - dm-upload-images: guard sleep_seconds.
    - ppcross_install: guard \$1 for the no-arg invocation path.

    Source help-steps/pre where color vars and error() were referenced
    without being defined:

    - dm-tbb-update: needed for color vars.
    - dm-git-commit-checkout-latest, dm-git-tag-checkout-latest: needed
      for color vars and error().

